WEBVTT

00:02.583 --> 00:04.125
TODAY'S FORECAST --
HEY, MID 70s!

00:04.125 --> 00:06.587
UNSEASONABLY WARM AND CLEAR
IN THE PACIFIC NORTHWEST.

00:06.587 --> 00:08.089
IT'S GONNA BE
A GREAT DAY, SEATTLE!

00:08.089 --> 00:09.760
Cristina: HE DOESN'T KNOW THAT.
HE'S AN IDIOT.

00:09.760 --> 00:12.053
Woman: IT SOUNDS LIKE
IT'S A GOOD DAY TO GET OUTSIDE.

00:12.053 --> 00:14.805
Cristina:
FOR ALL HE KNOWS, IT COULD BE
THE WORST DAY OF HIS LIFE.
WHY IS THAT ON?

00:14.805 --> 00:17.268
Woman: THANKS, LEN.
NEXT UP --
OH! UM, I WANTED
TO SEE THE WEATHER.

00:17.268 --> 00:18.399
[ TV CLICKS ]
I HAVE TO FLY TODAY.

00:18.399 --> 00:20.141
YOU'VE BEEN SAYING THAT
FOR TWO WEEKS.

00:20.141 --> 00:22.193
WELL, ONLY BECAUSE
LINK McNEIL KEPT GETTING CLOSE

00:22.193 --> 00:23.274
TO GETTING A HEART.

00:23.274 --> 00:24.525
I REALLY WANTED
TO SEE THAT THROUGH.

00:24.525 --> 00:27.198
I CAN'T PUT OFF ZURICH
ANYMORE.

00:27.198 --> 00:29.070
THERE IS A STAFF MEETING
ON MONDAY,

00:29.070 --> 00:31.992
AND IF I'M NOT THERE, IT'LL BE
A TERRIBLE FIRST IMPRESSION,

00:31.992 --> 00:33.954
AND I'LL LOSE CONTROL
BEFORE I START.

00:33.954 --> 00:35.616
SO...

00:35.616 --> 00:37.498
THIS IS GOODBYE THEN?

00:38.579 --> 00:40.291
LAST NIGHT WASN'T ENOUGH?

00:40.291 --> 00:41.502
NO. NO.

00:41.502 --> 00:42.963
COME ON. COME ON.
COME ON.

00:42.963 --> 00:44.795
OWEN, NO, NO.
YOU MADE ME LATE ALREADY.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.337
NO.
MEREDITH MADE YOU LATE.

00:46.337 --> 00:48.339
YOU WERE OUT DRINKING
TILL 2:00 IN THE MORNING.

00:48.339 --> 00:50.591
WELL, 'CAUSE THAT WAS
OUR BIG GOODBYE.

00:50.591 --> 00:53.013
OH, WE ARE NOT HAVING
A BIG GOODBYE HERE.

00:53.013 --> 00:54.975
I -- [ SIGHS ] I'M GONNA BE
AT THE HOSPITAL LATER

00:54.975 --> 00:56.387
TO CHECK ON
MY LAST CONDUIT KID.

00:56.387 --> 00:59.180
WE HAVE A BIG GOODBYE HERE,
AND THEN I'LL SEE YOU THERE,

00:59.180 --> 01:03.184
AND I'LL FEEL ALL...
"DUH, BYE, AGAIN."

01:03.184 --> 01:05.186
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
I-I-I GOT TO GO. I GOT TO GO.

01:05.186 --> 01:06.607
Cristina:
YOU KNOW HOW PEOPLE SAY,

01:06.607 --> 01:09.069
"WHO KNOWS? I COULD GET HIT
BY A BUS TOMORROW"?

01:09.069 --> 01:11.112
[ GROANS ]
THAT SEEMS
PRETTY FARFETCHED...

01:11.112 --> 01:14.495
OH, CRAP. OH, CRAP!
OH, NO! MY PHONE IS DEAD!

01:14.495 --> 01:16.577
...UNTIL YOU HAVE A FRIEND
WHO GOT HIT BY A BUS.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.789
AND I NEED
A EUROPEAN CHARGER.
CRISTINA --

01:18.789 --> 01:20.331
OH, NO, NOW I HAVE TO GO
TO THE STUPID MALL!

01:20.331 --> 01:22.203
[ SIGHS ]

01:22.203 --> 01:24.125
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

01:24.125 --> 01:27.258
THE POINT IS, WE NEVER KNOW
WHAT KIND OF DAY IS COMING.

01:27.258 --> 01:28.879
[ SIGHS ]
HOW IS EVERYBODY?

01:28.879 --> 01:31.172
AH, SO, ZOZO'S IN HER ROOM
GETTING DRESSED,

01:31.172 --> 01:33.804
AND THIS LITTLE GUY JUST POOPED,
SO THERE'S THAT.

01:33.804 --> 01:36.347
HOW WAS YOUR FLIGHT?
ROUGH, BUT -- MWAH!

01:36.347 --> 01:37.718
WE HAVE A PLACE TO LIVE
IN D.C.

01:37.718 --> 01:40.060
WE GOT THE TOWNHOUSE
IN FOGGY BOTTOM.

01:40.060 --> 01:41.352
WE GOT IT?!
WE CLOSE IN A MONTH.

01:41.352 --> 01:43.144
I JUST NEED YOU TO SIGN
THE PAPERWORK.

01:43.144 --> 01:45.316
WHAT IS TODAY?
IS TODAY TUESDAY?
TODAY IS THURSDAY.

01:45.316 --> 01:47.608
OH, GOOD.
THEN AMY'S GOT MY SURGERIES.

01:47.608 --> 01:50.030
I CAN SLEEP IN ALL DAY.
OKAY, BUT FIRST, THAT GUY
HAS A FOGGY BOTTOM,

01:50.030 --> 01:51.232
AND I CAN TAKE A LOOK
AT THESE TONIGHT.

01:51.232 --> 01:52.863
HEY, YOU WANT TO LOOK
AT THE BROCHURE AGAIN

01:52.863 --> 01:56.076
AND REMIND YOURSELF
HOW MUCH YOU LOVE IT?

01:56.076 --> 02:00.040
HMM.
OH, IT'S PRETTY!

02:00.040 --> 02:02.503
[CHUCKLES] IT'S THE FREAKING
BATMOBILE IS WHAT IT IS.

02:02.503 --> 02:03.834
IT'S EITHER THIS OR A BOAT.

02:03.834 --> 02:05.085
EVERYBODY AT THE PRACTICE
HAS A BOAT.

02:05.085 --> 02:06.547
ARE YOU REALLY A BOAT GUY?

02:06.547 --> 02:08.128
HOW SHOULD I KNOW?
I NEVER HAD A BOAT.

02:08.128 --> 02:09.510
MM.
OOH!

02:09.510 --> 02:11.212
ARE YOU LOOKING TO BUY
A ROAD-PENIS?

02:11.212 --> 02:12.343
IT'S THAT OR A BOAT.

02:12.343 --> 02:13.674
OH, NO, YOU DON'T SEEM
LIKE A BOAT GUY.

02:13.674 --> 02:15.716
WHAT ARE YOU HERE FOR?
MY FIRST ANOPLASTY.

02:15.716 --> 02:17.388
WOW.
IS LEBACKES GROOMING YOU?

02:17.388 --> 02:19.430
ARE YOU GONNA BE
DR. JUNIOR BUTTHOLE?

02:19.430 --> 02:21.722
[ Laughing ] OH, NO!
THAT'S WHAT THEY'LL CALL YOU.

02:21.722 --> 02:24.225
I WON'T HEAR THEM 'CAUSE I'LL
BE SQUEALING AWAY IN THIS.

02:24.225 --> 02:26.317
CONGRATULATIONS,
LIL' BUTTHOLE.
THANKS.

02:26.317 --> 02:27.688
Richard: ANY THOUGHT
ON WHO WILL FILL

02:27.688 --> 02:29.230
THE THREE EMPTY SEATS
ON THE BOARD?

02:29.230 --> 02:30.901
UH, IT'S ONLY ONE SEAT,
ACTUALLY.

02:30.901 --> 02:32.653
SHEPHERD AND GREY WILL KEEP
THEIR SEATS.

02:32.653 --> 02:34.575
THEY'LL TELECOMMUTE
FROM D.C. FOR MEETINGS.

02:34.575 --> 02:36.036
YANG SAYS
SHE WON'T HAVE TIME.

02:36.036 --> 02:37.578
I THINK SHE JUST WANTS
A CLEAN BREAK.

02:37.578 --> 02:39.280
SO THAT JUST LEAVES
HER SEAT OPEN.

02:39.280 --> 02:41.121
[ GASPS ]
MORNING, GENTLEMEN.

02:41.121 --> 02:42.663
YOU'LL BE HAPPY TO KNOW

02:42.663 --> 02:45.286
THAT FORMER BUBBLE BOY
BRADEN MORRIS

02:45.286 --> 02:47.498
HAD HIS FIRST FOLLOW-UP
WITH HIS PEDIATRICIAN.

02:47.498 --> 02:48.839
HE IS HEALTHY AS A HORSE.

02:48.839 --> 02:50.170
UH, I HAVE A CONSULT,
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.342
AH, YOU CAN STAY.
YOU SHOULD --

02:54.295 --> 02:55.466
WHAT'S UP?

02:55.466 --> 02:56.927
DISAPPOINTING NEWS,
ACTUALLY.

02:56.927 --> 02:58.299
THE FOUNDATION CUT
OUR BUDGET,

02:58.299 --> 03:01.682
SO WE ARE UNABLE TO CONTINUE
FUNDING YOUR GENOME LAB.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.564
OH, WELL,
WHO'S GONNA FUND IT, THEN?

03:03.564 --> 03:05.185
WE'RE SHUTTING IT DOWN
ACTUALLY.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.147
IT'S SIMPLY NOT PRODUCING THE
RESULTS THAT OTHER PROJECTS --

03:07.147 --> 03:09.069
DID YOU NOT JUST HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

03:09.069 --> 03:12.813
I-I GAVE
AN IMMUNODEFICIENT CHILD

03:12.813 --> 03:14.775
DEACTIVATED H.I.V.
AND SAVED HIM!

03:14.775 --> 03:17.408
AND ALMOST GOT THE HOSPITAL SUED
IN THE PROCESS.

03:17.408 --> 03:19.740
AND ALMOST LOST YOUR LICENSE
AND LANDED IN JAIL.

03:19.740 --> 03:21.952
SO IS THAT REALLY WHERE
YOU WANT TO PLANT YOUR FLAG?

03:21.952 --> 03:23.414
YES!

03:23.414 --> 03:25.286
AND SO SHOULD YOU!

03:25.286 --> 03:26.877
HEY, TWO YEARS AGO,

03:26.877 --> 03:28.829
I WAS WIPING YOUR BUTT
AND CHANGING YOUR DIAPER,

03:28.829 --> 03:30.751
AND NOW YOU WANT TO DO THIS
TO ME?

03:30.751 --> 03:32.753
N-NO, NO.
I-I WILL NOT STAND FOR IT.

03:32.753 --> 03:34.465
IT'S BUDGETARY,
AND IT'S DONE.

03:34.465 --> 03:35.596
WON'T STAND FOR IT!

03:35.596 --> 03:37.338
HEY, HAVE YOU TALKED
TO LEAH?

03:37.338 --> 03:38.639
OH. YEAH.

03:38.639 --> 03:39.890
SHE'S STILL ON HER COUCH,

03:39.890 --> 03:41.181
STILL DEPRESSED,
EATING EVERYTHING.

03:41.181 --> 03:42.393
HAS SHE SAID
WHAT SHE'S GONNA DO?

03:42.393 --> 03:44.345
WON'T EVEN TALK ABOUT IT --
CATATONIC.

03:44.345 --> 03:45.686
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:45.686 --> 03:47.608
JUST FINISHED AN ANEURYSM CLIP
WITH DR. SHEPHERD.

03:47.608 --> 03:48.809
SHEPHERD OR SHEPHERDESS?

03:48.809 --> 03:49.940
SHEPHERDESS.

03:49.940 --> 03:51.402
"SHEPHERDESS"? REALLY?

03:51.402 --> 03:53.404
UH, SORRY.
IT'S JUST VERY CONFUSING.

03:53.404 --> 03:54.945
I KIND OF LIKE IT --
SHEPHERDESS.

03:54.945 --> 03:57.818
OH, WELL, BEFORE, IT WAS JUST
"SHEPHERD'S LITTLE SISTER."

03:57.818 --> 03:58.909
[ LAUGHS ]

03:58.909 --> 04:01.412
EDWARDS, DO YOU LIKE
WORKING ON NEURO?

04:01.412 --> 04:03.203
DON'T EVER SAY THAT
TO ME AGAIN.

04:03.203 --> 04:04.705
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

04:04.705 --> 04:07.498
I E-MAILED DR. YANG TWICE
ABOUT THE CONDUIT BABIES,

04:07.498 --> 04:10.210
AND HER ONLY RESPONSE WAS,
"NOT YOUR PROBLEM."

04:10.210 --> 04:11.632
I'M THE HEAD OF CARDIO.
I'M HER BOSS.

04:11.632 --> 04:13.374
AND THE WAY THAT SHE TALKS TO ME
SOMETIMES --

04:13.374 --> 04:14.585
LOOK, DR. PIERCE, I --

04:14.585 --> 04:16.427
"MAGGIE." "MARGARET."

04:16.427 --> 04:18.839
[ SIGHS ]
"MAGGIE" IS FINE.

04:18.839 --> 04:20.551
DR. YANG WILL BE
COMING IN LATER TODAY

04:20.551 --> 04:22.383
FOR A FINAL CHECKUP
WITH HER CONDUIT BABY

04:22.383 --> 04:24.264
BEFORE SHE --
AND THEN SHE'S LEAVING?

04:24.264 --> 04:25.516
FOR GOOD?

04:25.516 --> 04:27.438
YES, YES, SHE WILL BE GONE
BY THE END OF THE DAY.

04:27.438 --> 04:28.649
[ SIGHS ]

04:28.649 --> 04:30.020
IS THAT IT?

04:30.020 --> 04:33.273
YES.
I HAVE A PATIENT IN PRE-OP.

04:35.025 --> 04:36.156
IT'S THAT WAY.

04:37.318 --> 04:39.900
I'M GETTING IT.
MM-HMM.

04:39.900 --> 04:41.201
[ SIGHS ]

04:41.201 --> 04:42.533
CHIEF.
MM-HMM?

04:42.533 --> 04:43.704
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

04:43.704 --> 04:45.205
YOU ARE.
PRIVATELY?

04:45.205 --> 04:47.247
UM, DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE TO GO
INTO, LIKE, A TRAUMA ROOM?

04:47.247 --> 04:49.169
[ SIGHS ]
SPIT IT OUT, KEPNER.
I'M PREGNANT.

04:50.080 --> 04:52.172
I KNOW IT'S SUDDEN
AND IT'S SOON,

04:52.172 --> 04:53.624
AND I KNOW
IT MAKES YOUR LIFE HELL,

04:53.624 --> 04:55.376
BUT I WILL WORK
UNTIL IT FALLS OUT OF ME.

04:55.376 --> 04:57.257
KEPNERS ARE BUILT
TO HAVE BABIES, SIR.

04:57.257 --> 04:59.089
W-WE'VE DROPPED THEM
IN FIELDS.

04:59.089 --> 05:00.341
KEPNER,
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

05:00.341 --> 05:01.682
[ LAUGHS ]
I'M THRILLED.

05:01.682 --> 05:03.344
CONGRATULATIONS.
THANK YOU.

05:03.344 --> 05:04.595
IT WAS EARLIER
THAN WE THOUGHT,

05:04.595 --> 05:06.136
BUT MY MOM ALWAYS SAYS
THAT IF YOU WAIT

05:06.136 --> 05:07.848
FOR THE PERFECT TIME
TO HAVE A BABY,

05:07.848 --> 05:09.229
THEN YOU'LL JUST DIE...
CHILDLESS.

05:09.229 --> 05:10.391
Diane:
IF YOU'RE JUST JOINING US...

05:10.391 --> 05:11.892
WE HAVE BREAKING NEWS...
TURN THAT UP.

05:11.892 --> 05:13.484
...OF AN ENORMOUS EXPLOSION.

05:13.484 --> 05:17.698
IT HAPPENED ONLY MINUTES AGO
AT SEATTLE'S MALL OF THE WOODS.

05:17.698 --> 05:20.320
WE ARE GETTING REPORTS
OF MASSIVE FATALITIES

05:20.320 --> 05:22.613
Woman: OH, MY GOSH!
EXPLOSION!
...AND SCORES
OF PEOPLE INJURED.

05:22.613 --> 05:25.035
Man: OH, MY GOSH!
OFFICIALS HAVE NOT YET
DETERMINED...

05:25.035 --> 05:26.497
PAGE ALL AVAILABLE SURGEONS.
CLEAR THE E.R.

05:26.497 --> 05:28.208
BRING THEM TO ME.
DISCHARGE ALL PATIENTS
WHO CAN BE.

05:28.208 --> 05:30.581
CANCEL ALL
ELECTIVE SURGERIES.
ADMITS --
LET'S GET THEM UPSTAIRS.

05:30.581 --> 05:32.082
I WANT A SECURITY LOCKDOWN
ON THIS FLOOR.

05:32.082 --> 05:33.584
I WANT ALL AVAILABLE BEDS
AND GURNEYS DOWN HERE.

05:33.584 --> 05:35.215
CALL BLOOD SERVICES.
I WANT ALL THE O-NEG THEY HAVE.

05:35.215 --> 05:36.417
THE CONCERN RIGHT NOW --

05:36.417 --> 05:38.419
AND WHAT
WE'RE ALL WONDERING IS --

05:38.419 --> 05:41.422
IS THIS AN ACT OF TERRORISM?

05:51.602 --> 05:53.103
Woman: SO IT'S CHEMICAL?
I'M NOT SAYING THAT.

05:53.103 --> 05:54.685
SOME PATIENTS ARE PRESENTING
WITH BLISTERS AND RASHES,

05:54.685 --> 05:55.686
BUT THE CAUSE IS NOT YET KNOWN.

05:55.686 --> 05:57.027
THIS COULD BE NOTHING,

05:57.027 --> 05:59.239
BUT WE ARE TAKING PROPER
DECONTAMINATION PRECAUTIONS.

05:59.239 --> 06:01.151
THE MAIN MESSAGE HERE

06:01.151 --> 06:03.824
IS THAT WE ARE FULLY EQUIPPED
TO TREAT THE INJURED.

06:03.824 --> 06:06.487
IF YOU'RE COMING TO THE HOSPITAL
TO LOOK FOR A LOVED ONE,

06:06.487 --> 06:08.489
IF, UH... [CLEARS THROAT]
[ SIREN WAILS ]

06:08.489 --> 06:10.991
IF YOU'VE, UH --
IF YOU'VE LOST SOMEONE, THEN...

06:10.991 --> 06:12.703
PLEASE STAY CLEAR
OF THE EMERGENCY ENTRANCE.

06:12.703 --> 06:14.334
COME STRAIGHT
TO THE MAIN ENTRANCE.

06:14.334 --> 06:15.796
THANK YOU.
Man:
ONE MORE QUESTION!

06:15.796 --> 06:17.418
[ MOANING ]

06:17.418 --> 06:19.500
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

06:19.500 --> 06:20.501
CHIEF HUNT?
HM?

06:20.501 --> 06:22.132
RAY PELLETIER,
HOMELAND SECURITY.

06:22.132 --> 06:24.054
THERE ARE SOME PATIENTS
WE NEED TO TALK TO.

06:24.054 --> 06:25.385
FOLLOW ME.

06:25.385 --> 06:27.267
OKAY, TAKE THIS ONE
TO TRAUMA FOUR NOW.

06:27.267 --> 06:28.639
Owen:
KEPNER, HOW ARE WE?

06:28.639 --> 06:30.511
GOOD. WE'VE TAKEN IN OVER 30
INJURED. MORE ON THE WAY.

06:30.511 --> 06:32.893
TRIAGE AREAS ARE LAID OUT --
REDS HERE, YELLOWS HERE,

06:32.893 --> 06:34.435
GREENS IN THE HALLWAY.
AND UPSTAIRS?

06:34.435 --> 06:37.317
WE'VE STARTED ROTATING O.R.s,
ONE SURGEON IN EACH,

06:37.317 --> 06:38.519
WITH STEADY TURNOVER.

06:38.519 --> 06:39.570
OKAY.
TALK TO THESE MEN.

06:39.570 --> 06:40.731
HELP THEM FIND
WHO THEY'RE LOOKING FOR.

06:40.731 --> 06:42.322
AND, KEPNER,
GET A MASK ON.

06:42.322 --> 06:44.284
OH, GOD. YES, SIR.
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

06:44.284 --> 06:45.656
THIS WAY, GUYS.

06:45.656 --> 06:49.530
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

06:49.530 --> 06:53.033
[ SIGHS ]

06:53.033 --> 06:54.625
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

06:54.625 --> 06:57.588
CRISTINA: Hi. You've reached
the phone of Dr. Cristina Yang.

06:57.588 --> 06:59.500
I'm --
[ KEYPAD BEEPS ]

07:02.673 --> 07:04.545
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:04.545 --> 07:06.346
O.R.s ONE THROUGH THREE
ARE GENERAL.

07:06.346 --> 07:07.468
WE'RE GONNA NEED MORE.

07:07.468 --> 07:08.969
NEURO'S IN FOUR,
AND CARDIO IS IN FIVE.

07:08.969 --> 07:10.180
WHO'S IN
THE CARDIO O.R.?

07:10.180 --> 07:11.512
PIERCE,
THE NEW CARDIO CHIEF.

07:11.512 --> 07:12.683
OKAY, YOU GUYS, UH,

07:12.683 --> 07:14.394
KEPNER NEEDS HELP
WITH TRIAGE DOWNSTAIRS.

07:14.394 --> 07:16.186
KAREV, YOU SEE YANG
THIS MORNING?

07:16.186 --> 07:17.518
NO.
WASN'T SHE WITH YOU?

07:17.518 --> 07:20.270
YEAH, SHE SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT GOING TO THE MALL.

07:20.270 --> 07:21.902
YOU GOT TO BE FREAKING
KIDDING ME.

07:21.902 --> 07:23.403
WE DON'T WORRY UNTIL
WE'RE SURE WE HAVE
SOMETHING TO WORRY ABOUT,

07:23.403 --> 07:24.485
BUT IF YOU SEE HER,
YOU LET ME KNOW, OKAY?

07:24.485 --> 07:26.026
DON'T TELL MER!
YEAH.

07:26.026 --> 07:27.067
YOUR AIRWAY LOOKS GOOD.

07:27.067 --> 07:28.529
THIS CUT WILL NEED TO BE
STITCHED UP.

07:28.529 --> 07:29.910
[ Crying ]
AND THE BLISTERS?

07:29.910 --> 07:31.121
[ GASPS ]
WHAT IS THIS?

07:31.121 --> 07:32.202
WE DON'T KNOW YET,

07:32.202 --> 07:33.494
BUT WE'RE RUNNING
SOME TESTS, OKAY?

07:33.494 --> 07:35.706
I CAN'T FIND HIM.
I-I LOOKED ALL OVER DOWN HERE.

07:35.706 --> 07:38.378
I LOOKED OUTSIDE.
I CAN'T FIND HIM.
April: WHO?

07:38.378 --> 07:39.419
LEO -- MY BOY.

07:39.419 --> 07:41.211
OUR LITTLE BOY --
HE WAS WITH ME.

07:41.211 --> 07:42.462
WE WERE BUYING SHOES
WHEN --

07:42.462 --> 07:44.424
MARILYN, I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
SOME SEDATION.

07:44.424 --> 07:46.927
JUST TRY TO BREATHE,
OKAY?

07:46.927 --> 07:48.799
WHAT DOES LEO LOOK LIKE?

07:48.799 --> 07:50.721
HE'S 10.
BROWN HAIR. IT'S LONG.

07:50.721 --> 07:52.553
IT'S TOO LONG.
HE WON'T, UH, CUT IT.

07:52.553 --> 07:54.434
BROWN EYES.
HE HAS BRACES.

07:54.434 --> 07:56.476
IF HE'S HERE,
WE'LL FIND HIM.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.148
SO, YOU SAID YOU'RE
31 WEEKS PREGNANT, LEANNE?

07:58.148 --> 07:59.600
UH-HUH.
HOMESTRETCH, HUH?

07:59.600 --> 08:01.562
I'M ACTUALLY
EXPECTING A BABY, TOO.

08:01.562 --> 08:02.653
IS THE BABY GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT?

08:02.653 --> 08:04.104
WE HAVE TO DO SURGERY
ON YOUR ARM,

08:04.104 --> 08:05.566
BUT IF YOUR BABY GOES INTO
ANY DISTRESS,

08:05.566 --> 08:07.407
WE'LL NEED TO DO A C-SECTION,
OKAY, LEANNE?

08:07.407 --> 08:09.449
NO, NO, NO, NO, IT'S TOO SOON.
SHE'S TOO LITTLE.

08:09.449 --> 08:10.450
NO, YOUR BABY'S GONNA BE
JUST FINE.

08:10.450 --> 08:12.452
IT'S NOT MY BABY.
SORRY. WHAT?

08:12.452 --> 08:14.665
IT'S SOMEONE ELSE'S BABY.
I-I'M A SURROGATE.

08:14.665 --> 08:16.456
CAN YOU PLEASE TRY
TO LET IT GET TO TERM?

08:16.456 --> 08:17.578
IT'S THEIR BABY.

08:17.578 --> 08:18.879
WE WILL DO
WHAT WE CAN.

08:18.879 --> 08:20.080
A-AND THEY'RE
A SUPER-NICE COUPLE,

08:20.080 --> 08:21.501
AND THEY TRUST ME,
AND IT'LL KILL THEM,

08:21.501 --> 08:23.253
AND I REALLY LIKE THEM.

08:23.253 --> 08:24.464
LEANNE, WE'RE GONNA TAKE CARE
OF YOU NOW, OKAY? DON'T WORRY.

08:24.464 --> 08:26.426
Amelia:
ONE, TWO, THREE!

08:26.426 --> 08:27.888
LET'S GET HER TO THE ICU.

08:27.888 --> 08:29.930
TURN THE ROOM OVER.
LET'S GO!

08:29.930 --> 08:32.392
Woman:
RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.
NEXT!

08:32.392 --> 08:34.054
WHEN DID YOU GET HERE?
AS SOON AS I FOUND OUT.
ARE YOU OKAY?

08:34.054 --> 08:35.395
Amelia: I'M FINE.
YOU WANT TO SWITCH OUT?

08:35.395 --> 08:36.597
NO.
YOU WANT TO SWITCH OUT?

08:36.597 --> 08:38.138
DEREK, YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE OVER YOUR SERVICE,

08:38.138 --> 08:39.309
LET ME TAKE OVER
YOUR SERVICE.

08:39.309 --> 08:40.731
NEXT PATIENT, PLEASE.
A 26-YEAR-OLD --

08:40.731 --> 08:42.733
LEFT FRONTOPARIETAL
SUBDURAL HEMATOMA.

08:42.733 --> 08:44.815
BURR HOLE'S NOT GONNA
DO THIS, SO WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA NEED TO DO --

08:44.815 --> 08:47.067
I'LL SEE
WHEN I GET IN THERE.

08:48.448 --> 08:50.450
Catherine: MAKE A PATH, PEOPLE!
COMING THROUGH!

08:50.450 --> 08:51.702
I GOT IT.

08:51.702 --> 08:54.454
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
ISN'T IT OBVIOUS?

08:54.454 --> 08:56.456
ACTUALLY, I CAME
TO VISIT MY SON.

08:56.456 --> 08:58.579
APPARENTLY, I'M GOING TO BE
A GRANDMOTHER.

08:58.579 --> 09:00.160
MM.
WEBBER, WE NEED TO
OPEN ANOTHER O.R.

09:00.160 --> 09:01.251
CAN YOU GO UP TO SIX?

09:01.251 --> 09:02.422
I'LL START
THROWING PATIENTS AT YOU.

09:02.422 --> 09:03.423
UH, ON MY WAY.

09:04.715 --> 09:08.338
IT'S A WEEKDAY, RIGHT?
SHOULDN'T YOU BE IN CLASS?

09:08.338 --> 09:09.549
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
AT THE MALL?

09:09.549 --> 09:11.051
WHERE'S NICKY?
WHERE'S MY FRIEND?

09:11.051 --> 09:12.633
NICKY'S GONE, MIKE.
IT'S JUST ME AND YOU.

09:12.633 --> 09:14.224
NOW, YOU WANT TO TALK TO ME?

09:14.224 --> 09:17.387
WHAT WAS IN YOUR FRIEND'S
BACKPACK?

09:17.387 --> 09:18.849
MIKE!

09:18.849 --> 09:20.560
HIS EARDRUMS ARE RUPTURED.
HE MAY NOT BE ABLE TO HEAR YOU.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.683
OKAY, HE'S COMING WITH ME.
GET HIS CLOTHES.

09:22.683 --> 09:24.775
YOU CAN'T TAKE HIM ANYWHERE.
WE HAVE TO WATCH HIM.

09:24.775 --> 09:26.396
YOU SAID HE ISN'T
BADLY INJURED, RIGHT?

09:26.396 --> 09:28.649
WHAT I SAID WAS, SO FAR,
HIS WORK-UP HAS BEEN NEGATIVE,

09:28.649 --> 09:30.861
BUT INTERNAL-BLAST INJURIES
TAKE A WHILE --
OKAY, SO, YOU'RE SAYING

09:30.861 --> 09:32.743
HE WAS LIKELY VERY CLOSE
TO THE BLAST?

09:32.743 --> 09:34.574
NO, WHAT I'M SAYING IS --
RIGHT NEXT TO IT?
WAS HE -- WAS HE RUNNING --

09:34.574 --> 09:36.496
WE NEED SOME HELP
IN HERE!

09:36.496 --> 09:37.658
Man: YOU GOT IT, DOCTOR.
HE'S OKAY.

09:37.658 --> 09:39.750
HE'S TACHYCARDIC.

09:39.750 --> 09:41.161
ABDOMEN'S RIGID.

09:41.161 --> 09:42.462
WE GOT TO GET HIM
TO THE O.R. RIGHT AWAY.

09:42.462 --> 09:43.754
MA'AM, WE DON'T KNOW
IF THIS IS OVER YET.

09:43.754 --> 09:45.545
IF HE DIES ON YOUR TABLE
BEFORE I QUESTION HIM,

09:45.545 --> 09:46.797
WE HAVE NOTHING LEFT.

09:46.797 --> 09:48.669
AND IF HE ISN'T THE GUY,
YOU HAVE A DEAD CIVILIAN

09:48.669 --> 09:50.510
ON YOUR HANDS
WHOSE CARE YOU OBSTRUCTED.

09:50.510 --> 09:51.672
MOVE!
MA'AM, PLEASE!

09:51.672 --> 09:53.053
IT'S "DOCTOR."
YOU'RE THE BOSS OUT THERE.

09:53.053 --> 09:55.015
I'M THE BOSS IN HERE.
GET OUT OF MY WAY.

09:56.516 --> 09:57.597
[ SIGHS ] LET 'EM BY.

09:59.059 --> 10:01.722
Nicole: I NEED SOME HELP HERE!
NOW!

10:01.722 --> 10:03.563
[ SIREN WAILING ]

10:03.563 --> 10:06.316
WHAT HAPPENED?
HE WAS WALKING AND TALKING,
AND HE JUST WENT DOWN.

10:06.316 --> 10:07.988
HIS AIRWAY IS CLEAR.
NO BREATH SOUNDS.

10:07.988 --> 10:09.319
I CAN'T FEEL A PULSE.

10:09.319 --> 10:11.071
GET A CRASH CART,
CHEST TUBE, AND CHEST TRAY NOW.

10:11.071 --> 10:12.362
HOW LONG'S HE BEEN DOWN?
ALMOST A MINUTE.

10:12.362 --> 10:14.154
CRAP.
HAS HE BEEN SPRAYED DOWN?
Man: NO, SIR!

10:14.154 --> 10:16.076
SPRAY HIM DOWN NOW!
I'M ON IT!

10:18.739 --> 10:20.160
EVERYWHERE!
GET HIM EVERYWHERE!

10:20.160 --> 10:21.912
THAT'S IT.

10:21.912 --> 10:23.794
HOLD IT.
HOLD IT. STOP.

10:23.794 --> 10:25.375
[ SIGHS ] DAMN IT.

10:25.375 --> 10:26.797
DAMN IT.
I NEED THAT CHEST TRAY!

10:26.797 --> 10:28.548
GET ME A CHEST TRAY NOW!

10:28.548 --> 10:30.380
Cristina: GOT IT.
HERE. HERE.

10:30.380 --> 10:32.803
OH, MY GOD.
THANK GOD YOU'RE HERE.

10:32.803 --> 10:35.215
OF COURSE I'M HERE.
HUNT SAID YOU WENT
TO THE MALL.

10:35.215 --> 10:36.967
NO, I DIDN'T HAVE TIME.
I WAS -- WHAT ARE WE DOING?

10:36.967 --> 10:38.679
SUDDEN LOSS OF VITALS WITH
PENETRATING INJURY TO THE CHEST.

10:38.679 --> 10:40.350
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
OPEN HIM UP.

10:40.350 --> 10:42.472
SHOULDN'T YOU DO IT?
NO, YOU'RE THERE.
YOU GOT IT. GO FOR IT.

10:44.394 --> 10:46.476
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT?

10:46.476 --> 10:48.478
I WAS GONNA GO
TO THE MALL.

10:58.158 --> 11:00.120
Alana:
DIANE, OFFICIALS ARE SEEKING
TO QUESTION THESE MEN

11:00.120 --> 11:02.953
SEEN ENTERING THE MALL MINUTES
BEFORE THE EXPLOSION OCCURRED.

11:02.953 --> 11:04.624
Diane: OF COURSE,
THE BIGGEST QUESTION IS,

11:04.624 --> 11:06.246
"COULD THERE BE MORE ATTACKS
ON THE WAY?"

11:06.246 --> 11:07.958
Alana: THAT'S RIGHT.
[ SIREN WAILING ]

11:07.958 --> 11:09.379
I-IN FACT,
SOME PEOPLE ARE WONDERING

11:09.379 --> 11:11.251
IF THIS COULD BE
A TERRORIST STRATEGY --

11:11.251 --> 11:13.173
TO SEND VICTIMS
TO THE HOSPITAL

11:13.173 --> 11:15.095
AND THEN TARGET
THE HOSPITAL ITSELF.

11:15.095 --> 11:17.217
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]
ALANA, SHOULD YOU
EVEN BE THERE?

11:17.217 --> 11:18.889
I KNOW, RIGHT? IT'S AN
INTENSELY DANGEROUS SITUATION.

11:18.889 --> 11:20.801
Woman:
WHAT DID SHE JUST SAY?
April:
TURN THAT TV OFF!

11:20.801 --> 11:22.682
NO, NO, I DID WORK HERE
LIKE TWO WEEKS AGO.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.935
NO, SHE'S OKAY.
LET HER THROUGH.
WHAT CAN I DO?

11:24.935 --> 11:26.897
April: UH, YELLOWS, REDS,
AND GREENS IN THE HALLWAY.

11:26.897 --> 11:28.228
ASSESS AND TREAT
WHAT YOU CAN.

11:28.228 --> 11:30.020
OKAY, BUT I DON'T --
I-I DON'T HAVE PRIVILEGES.

11:30.020 --> 11:32.152
I CAN'T OPERATE --
WHATEVER NEEDS TO BE DONE,
DO IT.

11:32.152 --> 11:34.274
AND IF YOU SEE A 10-YEAR-OLD BOY
WITH BROWN HAIR,

11:34.274 --> 11:36.026
BROWN EYES, AND BRACES,
COME FIND ME.

11:36.026 --> 11:38.158
Bailey: LET'S GO! LET'S GO!
Man: COMING THROUGH!

11:38.158 --> 11:39.579
LET'S GO! NEXT! HIM?

11:39.579 --> 11:42.322
HE'S GOT PERITONITIS, PROBABLY
FROM A PERF IN THE BOWEL.

11:42.322 --> 11:44.204
HEAD C.T.
SHOWS A PROBABLE TBI.

11:44.204 --> 11:45.916
I CALLED NEURO
FOR A CONSULT.

11:45.916 --> 11:47.167
Bailey: OKAY.

11:47.167 --> 11:49.880
OKAY -- OH, BAILEY,
DHS WANTS TO SPEAK WITH HIM.

11:49.880 --> 11:51.251
HE'S A POSSIBLE SUSPECT.

11:51.251 --> 11:53.543
SO, UH, YOU PAGE ME
WHEN YOU FINISH.

11:53.543 --> 11:54.714
GOT IT.

11:54.714 --> 11:56.096
[ ELECTRICITY ZAPS,
MONITOR BEEPING ]

11:56.096 --> 11:58.678
Callie:
TRANSRADIAL AMPUTATION --

11:58.678 --> 12:00.640
BELOW THE ELBOW, AT LEAST.

12:00.640 --> 12:02.302
WHY WOULD THEY HIT
A SHOPPING MALL?

12:02.302 --> 12:03.513
THERE'S NOTHING THERE.

12:03.513 --> 12:05.145
Stephanie: EXCEPT PEOPLE --
REGULAR PEOPLE.

12:05.145 --> 12:06.306
Jackson:
THEY WANT TO SCARE US.

12:06.306 --> 12:07.687
IT'S THE SCARIEST THING
WE CAN THINK OF.

12:07.687 --> 12:09.479
HAS THAT RASH SHOWN UP
ON ANY OF OUR DOCTORS YET?

12:09.479 --> 12:11.611
NOT YET, WHICH IS GOOD. IT MEANS
IT MIGHT NOT BE AIRBORNE.

12:11.611 --> 12:13.613
THE NEWS SAID THEY MIGHT BE
TARGETING HOSPITALS NOW --

12:13.613 --> 12:16.236
OH, EDWARDS,
SHUT YOUR MOUTH, PLEASE.
I'M JUST SAYING.

12:16.236 --> 12:18.028
WHOA! OH!

12:18.028 --> 12:19.529
OH, DID HER WATER
JUST BREAK?

12:19.529 --> 12:21.782
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
THE BABY'S IN DISTRESS.

12:21.782 --> 12:24.624
LATE DECELS ON
THE FETAL HEART MONITOR.
WE NEED O.B.
DOWN HERE, STAT!

12:24.624 --> 12:25.956
AND PAGE DR. ROBBINS.

12:25.956 --> 12:28.208
TELL HER WE MIGHT BE
DELIVERING A PREMIE IN HERE.

12:28.208 --> 12:31.001
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
I THOUGHT YOU HAD A BIG MEETING.

12:31.001 --> 12:33.043
THEY BLEW UP SEATTLE, MER.
I CAN'T LEAVE.

12:33.043 --> 12:35.085
YOU SHOULD. NO ONE HAS A BEEF
WITH SWITZERLAND.

12:35.085 --> 12:36.636
SO, WE'RE GOING TO D.C.

12:36.636 --> 12:39.179
UM, WE SIGN PAPERS
ON THE TOWNHOUSE TONIGHT.

12:39.179 --> 12:41.141
IT'S NICE.
IT'S GONNA BE GOOD.

12:42.592 --> 12:45.475
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

12:45.475 --> 12:47.477
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.
PEOPLE DO THIS.

12:47.477 --> 12:50.100
ARE YOU? HAPPY FOR ME?
I GOT TO GO TO THE O.R.

12:50.100 --> 12:52.602
ALEX GAVE A KID
AN EMERGENCY THORACOTOMY.

12:54.064 --> 12:55.105
WATCH MY FINGER.

12:55.105 --> 12:57.777
I CAN'T SEE OUT OF IT.
IS IT GONE?

12:57.777 --> 13:00.160
NO, NO,
IT'S DEFINITELY THERE.

13:00.160 --> 13:01.571
IT'S ORBITAL COMPARTMENT
SYNDROME.

13:01.571 --> 13:03.243
GLOVE ME.
HEY. ARE YOU OKAY?

13:03.243 --> 13:04.825
YOU HAVE A LITTLE BLOOD
BEHIND YOUR EYE,

13:04.825 --> 13:06.246
AND I'M GONNA RELEASE THAT.

13:06.246 --> 13:08.208
THIS IS GONNA STING A LITTLE.

13:09.709 --> 13:12.252
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

13:14.044 --> 13:16.046
OKAY.

13:16.046 --> 13:17.587
NOW LOOK AT HIS FINGER.

13:17.587 --> 13:19.129
[ Weakly ] OKAY.

13:19.129 --> 13:20.050
[ SNIP ]

13:23.183 --> 13:24.845
OKAY.

13:24.845 --> 13:27.347
[ SQUISHING ]

13:27.347 --> 13:28.808
NOW OPEN FOR ME.

13:32.022 --> 13:35.195
I'M STARTING
TO SEE SOMETHING.

13:37.567 --> 13:39.199
I CAN SEE.

13:39.199 --> 13:40.280
THANK YOU!

13:40.280 --> 13:42.112
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
YOU GOT IT.

13:42.112 --> 13:43.533
ROSS!
I NEED YOU IN THE O.R.!

13:50.210 --> 13:52.252
HEY!
DOES THAT KID HAVE BRACES?

13:52.252 --> 13:54.875
HEY, HEY, LISTEN. YANG,
I JUST GOT A CALL FROM UNOS.

13:54.875 --> 13:56.506
THEY'VE BEEN TRYING
TO REACH YOU.

13:56.506 --> 13:58.048
OH, MY PHONE IS DEAD.

13:58.048 --> 14:00.050
A HEART'S BECOME AVAILABLE
THAT'S A MATCH FOR LINK McNEIL.

14:00.050 --> 14:01.341
NOW?

14:01.341 --> 14:02.632
WE TELL THEM TO DO IT
AT SEATTLE PRES, RIGHT,

14:02.632 --> 14:04.014
BECAUSE THERE'S NO --
NO, NO, NO, SEND IT HERE.

14:04.014 --> 14:08.058
NO, I-I-I GOT TO DO IT HERE.
TELL THE McNEILS TO COME.

14:08.058 --> 14:11.731
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:19.189 --> 14:22.822
Diane: ...CENTER OF THE CRISIS
AT GREY-SLOAN MEMORIAL.

14:22.822 --> 14:24.614
BYRON, WHAT CAN YOU TELL US?

14:24.614 --> 14:27.157
WHAT HAVE YOU LEARNED
AT THE HOSPITAL?

14:27.157 --> 14:29.199
RIGHT, DIANE,
THERE'S CONCERN NOW

14:29.199 --> 14:31.912
THAT THE SKIN REACTIONS
ON PATIENTS WE'RE HEARING ABOUT

14:31.912 --> 14:33.954
COULD POSSIBLY BE CAUSED
BY RADIATION

14:33.954 --> 14:35.956
FROM A SO-CALLED DIRTY BOMB.
DAMN IT.

14:35.956 --> 14:37.958
AND THE FEAR IS IT MIGHT NOT BE
AS EASILY TREATABLE

14:37.958 --> 14:40.090
AS AN ATTACK FROM CHEMICALS,
AS WE PREVIOUSLY THOUGHT,

14:40.090 --> 14:42.092
BUT THE FACT IS --
THE FACT IS,
YOU DON'T KNOW.

14:42.092 --> 14:44.094
OH, UH, HERE'S
THE CHIEF OF SURGERY.

14:44.094 --> 14:45.635
YOU ARE LYING
TO THEM NOW.

14:45.635 --> 14:47.968
YOU ARE SAYING ANTHRAX.
YOU ARE SAYING RADIATION.

14:47.968 --> 14:49.219
NOBODY ELSE IS.

14:49.219 --> 14:51.972
THE FACT IS WE DON'T KNOW
HOW BAD THIS IS, OKAY?

14:51.972 --> 14:55.515
SO STOP WONDERING OUT LOUD,
REPORT WHAT YOU KNOW,

14:55.515 --> 14:57.687
AND STOP SCARING PEOPLE
FOR NO REASON.

14:57.687 --> 14:59.609
WHAT -- I MEAN,
WHO LET YOU IN HERE?!

14:59.609 --> 15:01.401
GET OUT. STOP.
TURN OFF THE CAMERA.

15:01.401 --> 15:02.732
[ STATIC CRACKLES ]

15:02.732 --> 15:04.734
WELL, WE SEEM
TO HAVE LOST BYRON THERE.

15:04.734 --> 15:07.117
TENSIONS SEEM
TO BE RUNNING PRETTY HIGH,

15:07.117 --> 15:11.031
AS ONE WOULD EXPECT
IN SUCH A DANGEROUS SITUATION.

15:11.031 --> 15:12.622
STAY WITH US
FOR COMPLETE COVERAGE.

15:12.622 --> 15:14.034
WE WILL BE RIGHT BACK.

15:19.919 --> 15:22.302
Arizona: I'M READY.
WHERE'S THE O.B.?
Jackson: UH, NO SHOW,
BUT I PREPPED HER FOR THEM.

15:22.302 --> 15:24.754
Stephanie:
DECELS ARE REALLY FREQUENT.
Callie: YOU NEED TO GET
THAT BABY OUT OF THERE NOW.

15:24.754 --> 15:27.177
Arizona: WELL,
WHERE THE HELL'S THE O.B.?
THE BABY'S DOWN
TO 60 BEATS PER MINUTE.

15:27.177 --> 15:28.348
ALL RIGHT, AVERY,
YOU'RE GONNA HELP ME.

15:28.348 --> 15:29.759
50 BEATS AND SUSTAINED.
I NEED A 10 BLADE.

15:29.759 --> 15:32.392
OKAY, HANG ON, SWEETIE.
LET'S GET YOU OUT OF THERE.

15:32.392 --> 15:33.643
Shane:
SHE'LL WANT A STAPLER.

15:33.643 --> 15:37.767
Cristina: WE'VE ISOLATED
THE HILUM -- STAPLER.

15:37.767 --> 15:40.440
HOW ARE YOU GONNA
COPE WITH IT?

15:40.440 --> 15:42.692
Alex: WITH WHAT?
THE BOREDOM.

15:42.692 --> 15:45.775
MAKING BUTTHOLES WILL BE
YOUR WHOLE CAREER.

15:45.775 --> 15:48.618
HOW WILL YOU NOT
STICK YOUR HEAD IN THE OVEN?

15:48.618 --> 15:50.870
Alex: SCREW YOU.
I'LL CRY ABOUT IT ON MY BOAT.

15:50.870 --> 15:52.622
Shane:
GET A RELOAD READY.

15:52.622 --> 15:53.994
Cristina: YEAH, RIGHT,
YOU JUST SAW A KID,

15:53.994 --> 15:56.456
KNEW HE HAD A HEMOTHORAX,
REACHED IN, AND FIXED IT.

15:56.456 --> 15:57.667
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NEVER
GONNA DO THAT AGAIN.

15:57.667 --> 15:59.629
SAVING KIDS
WITH PING-PONG BALLS

15:59.629 --> 16:03.043
OR MAKING AN END STOMA
WITH AN APPENDIX -- STAPLER.

16:03.043 --> 16:05.585
HOW DID YOU EVEN KNOW
I DID THAT?

16:05.585 --> 16:07.087
YOU THINK I WASN'T
PAYING ATTENTION

16:07.087 --> 16:08.298
TO YOU PROVING ME WRONG?

16:08.298 --> 16:10.180
I MEAN, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE COMPETENT --

16:10.180 --> 16:11.551
WELL, NO.

16:11.551 --> 16:13.263
WHEN YOU GOT HERE,
I THOUGHT YOU WERE AN IMBECILE,

16:13.263 --> 16:15.645
BUT YOU GOT COMPETENT,
LIKE A DECENT HANDYMAN.

16:15.645 --> 16:19.229
BUT EVENTUALLY, I HAD TO ACCEPT
THAT YOU WERE GOOD --

16:19.229 --> 16:22.062
GOOD HANDS, AND YOU THINK FAST,
ACT FASTER.

16:22.062 --> 16:24.274
I MEAN, YOU'LL NEVER BE
AS GOOD AS ME,

16:24.274 --> 16:26.656
BUT YOU'RE VERY, VERY GOOD.

16:26.656 --> 16:29.069
OKAY, LET'S, UH, GET READY
FOR THE LEAK TEST.

16:29.069 --> 16:31.821
IRRIGATION?
THANK YOU, SHANE.

16:31.821 --> 16:34.244
AND YOU'RE PUTTING
ALL THAT TALENT IN A DRAWER.

16:34.244 --> 16:35.875
SO MAYBE YOU ARE
AN IMBECILE.

16:35.875 --> 16:38.208
OH, GOD, WHAT A RELIEF.
I'M STILL RIGHT.

16:39.749 --> 16:41.461
Maggie: DR. YANG,
DID YOU SCHEDULE

16:41.461 --> 16:43.623
A PEDIATRIC HEART TRANSPLANT
TO COME HERE TODAY?

16:43.623 --> 16:45.425
OH, HEY, YES. UH, GOOD.
ARE THE McNEILS HERE?

16:45.425 --> 16:47.047
WHY? WHY WOULD YOU THINK
THAT WE COULD DO --

16:47.047 --> 16:48.628
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
HE'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM.

16:48.628 --> 16:49.799
IT IS MY DEPARTMENT,
AND I'LL DECIDE

16:49.799 --> 16:51.131
WHAT SHOULD BE SENT OUT
TO OTHER HOSP--

16:51.131 --> 16:52.592
I'M A LITTLE BUSY HERE,

16:52.592 --> 16:54.724
SO CAN YOU JUST TELL ME
WHERE I CAN DO THE TRANSPLANT?

16:54.724 --> 16:56.636
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

16:58.768 --> 17:00.230
I'VE JUST FINISHED
IN O.R. THREE.

17:00.230 --> 17:01.771
YOU CAN DO YOUR TRANSPLANT
IN THERE.

17:01.771 --> 17:03.853
GREAT! UH, CAN YOU, UH, SEE
IF LINK McNEIL IS HERE YET

17:03.853 --> 17:05.645
AND, UM, PREP HIM FOR ME?
THANK YOU.

17:07.777 --> 17:09.699
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

17:09.699 --> 17:12.742
SERIOUSLY, THOUGH.
LINK McNEIL -- TODAY?

17:12.742 --> 17:15.115
I JUST NEED SOMETHING
TO FEEL FINISHED.

17:15.115 --> 17:16.656
SHANE CAN CLOSE FOR ME.
Shane: MM-HMM.

17:16.656 --> 17:18.748
Alex: ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT HIM
TO CLOSE THIS KID?

17:18.748 --> 17:20.080
I TAUGHT SHANE
HOW TO CLOSE.

17:20.080 --> 17:22.001
THERE WON'T EVEN BE A SCAR,
WILL THERE, SHANE?

17:22.001 --> 17:23.253
Shane: NOPE.
MNH-MNH.

17:24.584 --> 17:26.256
SUCTION.
[ LIQUID SUCKING ]

17:26.256 --> 17:28.798
Arizona: AVERY, I'M
CUTTING THE UTERUS, SO
PULL UP ON THOSE CLAMPS.

17:28.798 --> 17:30.760
Jackson: GOT IT.
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

17:30.760 --> 17:34.053
OKAY, NOW REACH IN HERE
AND PULL AWAY FROM ME.

17:34.053 --> 17:36.516
YOU GOT TO --
YOU GOT TO PULL HARDER.

17:36.516 --> 17:38.768
TUG IT, AVERY!
OKAY, YEAH. THERE. THERE.

17:38.768 --> 17:40.390
[ BABY CRYING ]
OH. OH. OKAY.

17:40.390 --> 17:41.601
ALL RIGHT, I GOT IT.

17:41.601 --> 17:43.062
CLAMP AND CUT THE CORD.

17:44.984 --> 17:47.147
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, YOU GOT HER.

17:47.147 --> 17:48.448
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

17:48.448 --> 17:49.819
OKAY. YOU'RE OKAY.

17:49.819 --> 17:51.611
Jackson:
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

17:53.823 --> 17:55.995
YOU'RE OKAY.

17:55.995 --> 17:57.827
I GOT YOU.

17:57.827 --> 17:59.749
I GOT YOU.

18:02.162 --> 18:04.624
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:04.624 --> 18:06.166
HOW LONG
TILL WE CAN HAVE HIM?

18:06.166 --> 18:07.757
I HAVE TO GET HIM TO RECOVERY
TO MAKE SURE HE'S OKAY.

18:07.757 --> 18:09.048
DOCTOR, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND

18:09.048 --> 18:11.090
THE NATURE
OF WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE!

18:11.090 --> 18:12.802
DO YOU WANT HIM HEALTHY ENOUGH
TO ANSWER YOUR QUESTIONS?
[ CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS ]

18:12.802 --> 18:14.804
YEAH.
[ SIGHS ]

18:16.636 --> 18:19.179
RIGHT.

18:19.179 --> 18:20.560
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

18:20.560 --> 18:21.811
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.

18:21.811 --> 18:23.353
WAIT.
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

18:23.353 --> 18:24.894
SITUATION'S CHANGED. HE'S NO
LONGER A SUBJECT OF INTEREST.

18:24.894 --> 18:26.226
THAT'S ALL
I CAN TELL YOU.

18:26.226 --> 18:27.397
BUT WHAT ABOUT HIM?

18:27.397 --> 18:29.279
DON'T YOU THINK
YOU OWE HIM AN APOLOGY?

18:29.279 --> 18:32.031
DOCTOR, YOU HAVE A VERY TOUGH
JOB KEEPING PEOPLE ALIVE.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.615
I DO, TOO.

18:38.158 --> 18:39.739
DRY-CLEANING FLUID?
THE CDC REPORT SAYS

18:39.739 --> 18:41.621
THAT'S WHAT'S CAUSING
THE PATIENTS' BLISTERS.

18:41.621 --> 18:43.663
THERE WAS A BIG DRY CLEANER
AT THE MALL.

18:43.663 --> 18:45.295
VICTIMS WERE LAYING
IN PUDDLES OF THE STUFF.

18:45.295 --> 18:47.457
PROLONGED SKIN EXPOSURE
CAN CAUSE RASHES.

18:47.457 --> 18:49.839
SO IT WASN'T A CHEMICAL ATTACK?
IT WAS JUST A BOMB?

18:49.839 --> 18:51.751
DR. HUNT,
YOU'LL WANT TO SEE THIS.

18:51.751 --> 18:53.923
Diane: AND WE WILL BE
BRINGING YOU MORE INFORMATION

18:53.923 --> 18:55.014
AS IT BECOMES AVAILABLE.

18:55.014 --> 18:56.386
WE REPEAT NOW --

18:56.386 --> 18:58.638
INVESTIGATORS HAVE DETERMINED
AT THIS HOUR

18:58.638 --> 19:00.220
THAT
THE MALL OF THE WOODS BLAST

19:00.220 --> 19:02.892
WAS CAUSED
BY A GAS-MAIN EXPLOSION.

19:02.892 --> 19:05.975
OFFICIALS SAY THEY FOUND
NO EVIDENCE OF FOUL PLAY

19:05.975 --> 19:09.269
AND THAT FEARS OF A TERRORIST
THREAT WERE UNFOUNDED.

19:09.269 --> 19:11.321
[ SIGHS HEAVILY ]
THANK YOU, JESUS.

19:11.321 --> 19:13.112
SEATTLE POWER OFFICIALS SAY
THE GAS MAIN RAN DIRECTLY...
YEP. SECOND THAT.

19:13.112 --> 19:15.405
...UNDER THE MALL'S EAST END...
ALL RIGHT, CHIEF,
WHAT'S NEXT?

19:15.405 --> 19:16.616
HOW DOES THIS CHANGE
WHAT WE'RE DOING?

19:16.616 --> 19:17.657
IT CHANGES NOTHING,
KEPNER.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.158
THERE WAS STILL
AN EXPLOSION.

19:19.158 --> 19:20.700
THE WOUNDED ARE STILL WOUNDED,
AND PEOPLE ARE STILL LOST.

19:20.700 --> 19:22.912
Leah: HEY. I THINK I FOUND
YOUR BROWN-HAIRED KID.

19:22.912 --> 19:24.834
ROSS AND KAREV
WERE TAKING HIM INTO SURGERY,

19:24.834 --> 19:26.706
AND HE'S JUST
ON HIS WAY OUT.
OH, THANK GOD.

19:26.706 --> 19:27.837
I-I NEED TO GO
TELL HIS PARENTS.

19:27.837 --> 19:28.838
GO.
Sabine: DR. HUNT.

19:28.838 --> 19:31.000
SABINE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:31.000 --> 19:32.882
UH, THEY TOLD US
THERE'S A HEART FOR LINK.

19:32.882 --> 19:34.674
TODAY?
THEY TOLD YOU TO COME HERE?

19:34.674 --> 19:36.256
I KNOW, BUT DR. YANG TOLD US
TO COME RIGHT OVER.

19:36.256 --> 19:38.508
YOU SPOKE TO HER?
YOU SPOKE TO DR. YANG?

19:38.508 --> 19:39.889
YES.
SHE TOLD US TO COME.

19:39.889 --> 19:41.010
[ SIGHS ]

19:41.010 --> 19:42.682
S-SHOULD WE GO
SOMEWHERE ELSE?

19:42.682 --> 19:44.854
I KNOW THAT THERE'S SO MANY
PEOPLE HERE THAT NEED HELP --

19:44.854 --> 19:46.606
NO, NO, NO, NO.
UH, LINK IS GONNA BE FINE.

19:46.606 --> 19:48.648
[ SIGHS ]
EVERYONE'S GONNA BE FINE.

19:48.648 --> 19:50.189
COME WITH ME.
I'LL HELP YOU FIND HER.

19:50.189 --> 19:52.902
Ben: DR. HUNT!
WE NEED YOU HERE, STAT!

19:52.902 --> 19:54.904
THEY DUG HER OUT.
CODED TWICE IN THE FIELD.

19:54.904 --> 19:56.656
PENETRATING TRAUMA
TO THE ABDOMEN.

19:56.656 --> 19:58.238
OKAY, WE NEED TAKE HER
STRAIGHT UP.

19:58.238 --> 20:00.700
LET'S CALL AHEAD,
AND LET'S CLEAR AN O.R.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.702
OH, UM, TAKE MRS. McNEIL.
HELP HER FIND DR. YANG.

20:02.702 --> 20:05.585
AND, MURPHY?
THANK YOU FOR COMING IN.

20:07.327 --> 20:08.828
April:
HE'S STILL INTUBATED.

20:08.828 --> 20:10.209
HE'S HAD HIS LEFT LUNG
REMOVED,

20:10.209 --> 20:12.171
BUT DR. YANG SAYS
HE'LL RECOVER JUST FINE.

20:12.171 --> 20:15.004
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

20:18.388 --> 20:20.219
THAT'S --
THAT'S NOT HIM.

20:21.891 --> 20:25.144
[ GASPS ]
THAT'S -- THAT'S NOT OUR SON.

20:32.732 --> 20:36.446
[ SIGHS ]
FOUR BY FOURS.

20:36.446 --> 20:38.237
FOUR BY FOURS.

20:38.237 --> 20:40.490
APRIL, WHERE DO YOU KEEP
THE FOUR BY FOURS?

20:40.490 --> 20:42.622
[ Crying ] OH, HI.
YOU'RE HERE. HI.

20:42.622 --> 20:45.455
WHAT'S WRONG?
[ WHIMPERS ]

20:45.455 --> 20:48.578
[ GASPS ]
IT WAS A SHOPPING MALL.

20:50.460 --> 20:52.922
DIDN'T YOU HEAR?
IT WASN'T TERRORISTS.

20:52.922 --> 20:54.674
BUT THAT'S
WHAT WE THOUGHT.

20:54.674 --> 20:56.085
WE LIVE IN A WORLD

20:56.085 --> 20:59.339
WHERE THAT IS THE FIRST THOUGHT
THAT CROSSES OUR MINDS.

20:59.339 --> 21:01.090
I DON'T THINK I CAN DO IT.

21:01.090 --> 21:03.343
I DON'T THINK
I CAN RAISE A CHILD

21:03.343 --> 21:07.266
IN A WORLD WHERE THEY COULD DIE
GOING TO BUY NEW SHOES.

21:07.266 --> 21:08.728
I REMEMBER
WHEN I WAS 10 YEARS OLD,

21:08.728 --> 21:13.192
SITTING IN A RESTAURANT
WITH MY FATHER, GETTING WAFFLES.

21:13.192 --> 21:15.104
I LOVED WAFFLES.

21:15.104 --> 21:17.317
I DIDN'T LIKE EGGS --
STILL DON'T.

21:17.317 --> 21:20.199
THIS WAS 1960, IN TEXAS,
IN A TOWN SO SMALL

21:20.199 --> 21:22.992
IT PROBABLY HAS FORGOTTEN
ITS OWN NAME BY NOW.

21:22.992 --> 21:24.324
AND I REMEMBER

21:24.324 --> 21:28.287
SOME IGNORANT YOUNG MEN
TELLING US TO LEAVE,

21:28.287 --> 21:30.580
DUMPING MY FATHER'S FOOD
IN HIS LAP,

21:30.580 --> 21:32.792
THROWING HOT COFFEE
ON HIM.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.674
WAS I SCARED? YES.

21:34.674 --> 21:36.336
I BEGGED HIM
TO TAKE ME OUT OF THERE.

21:36.336 --> 21:37.507
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HE SAID TO ME?

21:37.507 --> 21:38.918
WHAT?

21:38.918 --> 21:42.091
"NOT UNTIL AFTER YOU FINISH
YOUR EGGS, YOUNG LADY."

21:42.091 --> 21:44.974
[ LAUGHS ]

21:44.974 --> 21:47.387
WHAT -- WHAT DID THEY DO?
WHAT HAPPENED?

21:47.387 --> 21:49.188
NOTHING.

21:49.188 --> 21:51.270
THEY WENT ON
TO BOTHER SOMEBODY ELSE.

21:52.482 --> 21:56.986
HE WASN'T AFRAID,
SO THEY DIDN'T HAVE ANY POWER.

21:56.986 --> 22:02.031
APRIL, THERE'S ALWAYS
GONNA BE STUPID PEOPLE.

22:02.031 --> 22:03.863
THERE'S ALWAYS GONNA BE
ACCIDENTS.

22:03.863 --> 22:05.575
BUT THAT'S NOT
WHAT DEFEATS YOU.

22:05.575 --> 22:07.407
IT'S THE FEAR.

22:07.407 --> 22:10.410
NOW, IF YOU HAD TOLD ME
ON THAT DAY IN 1960

22:10.410 --> 22:12.622
THAT I WOULD HAVE THE JOB
THAT I HAVE TODAY,

22:12.622 --> 22:14.043
THE CHILD THAT I HAVE,

22:14.043 --> 22:15.415
I WOULD HAVE LAUGHED
TILL I CRIED.

22:15.415 --> 22:18.418
IT SEEMED
BEYOND IMPOSSIBLE.

22:18.418 --> 22:23.132
BUT THIS IS THE WAY
THE WORLD CHANGES, SWEETHEART --

22:23.132 --> 22:27.136
GOOD PEOPLE RAISING
THEIR BABIES RIGHT.

22:29.599 --> 22:31.350
NOW, COME ON.
WHERE ARE THE FOUR BY FOURS?

22:31.350 --> 22:33.232
WE GOT THINGS TO DO.
[ Chuckling ] OKAY.

22:33.232 --> 22:34.974
WE GOT WORK TO DO!

22:34.974 --> 22:36.355
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

22:36.355 --> 22:37.567
[ DOOR OPENS ]

22:37.567 --> 22:38.898
Cristina:
DID MORE COME IN?

22:38.898 --> 22:40.860
NO, IT'S SLOWING DOWN.
WHAT ARE YOU STILL DOING HERE?

22:40.860 --> 22:42.241
WHAT TIME IS YOUR FLIGHT?

22:42.241 --> 22:43.903
I CAN'T LEAVE, MEREDITH.
THEY JUST BOMBED SEATTLE.

22:43.903 --> 22:45.445
NO, THEY DIDN'T.
NO ONE DID.

22:45.445 --> 22:47.366
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT --
GAS MAIN.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.659
SO, NO DIFFERENT
THAN A TRAIN DERAILMENT

22:49.659 --> 22:51.991
OR A FERRY-BOAT CRASH,
SO YOU CAN GO.

22:53.332 --> 22:54.704
WHEN I HEARD
IT WAS THE MALL,

22:54.704 --> 22:56.255
YOU KNOW
WHAT I THOUGHT OF?

22:56.255 --> 22:59.168
I THOUGHT ABOUT THE TIME
THAT CALLIE AND I PLAYED HOOKEY

22:59.168 --> 23:01.050
AND WE BOUGHT ALL THE FURNITURE
FOR THE FIREHOUSE.

23:01.050 --> 23:02.341
WHAT TIME IS YOUR PLANE?

23:02.341 --> 23:03.883
[ SIGHS ]
TWO HOURS.

23:03.883 --> 23:06.345
BUT LINK McNEIL HAS GOT A HEART,
AND I HAVE TO DO THAT FIRST.

23:06.345 --> 23:07.637
NO, THE NEW HEAD OF CARDIO
CAN DO THAT.

23:07.637 --> 23:10.349
YOU DON'T HAVE THE TIME.

23:10.349 --> 23:11.721
PLUS,
YOU'LL HAVE TO RE-SCRUB.

23:11.721 --> 23:13.062
WHAT --
SO THERE'S THAT.

23:13.062 --> 23:14.063
MEREDITH!

23:14.063 --> 23:15.435
YOU HAVE BEEN STALLING
FOR TWO WEEKS.

23:15.435 --> 23:16.646
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I HAVE TO --

23:16.646 --> 23:19.398
I HAVE TO
FINISH SOMETHING HERE.

23:19.398 --> 23:22.942
NOTHING FEELS FINISHED.
NONE OF IT FEELS FINISHED.

23:22.942 --> 23:25.865
OWEN AND I...

23:25.865 --> 23:27.286
[ LAUGHS ]

23:27.286 --> 23:31.581
WE SPLIT...OVER SOMETHING
THAT HASN'T EVEN HAPPENED.

23:31.581 --> 23:35.204
AND WE NEVER EVEN SPLIT UP.

23:35.204 --> 23:36.375
AND Y--

23:36.375 --> 23:37.997
[ SIGHS ]

23:37.997 --> 23:40.960
[ Voice breaking ]
YOU AND I ARE NOT FINISHED.

23:43.342 --> 23:45.595
GEORGE IS DEAD,
AND IZZIE IS GONE,

23:45.595 --> 23:49.348
AND IT IS SUPPOSED TO BE
YOU AND ME AND ALEX.

23:49.348 --> 23:51.971
AND NOW NOTHING IS FINISHED.

23:51.971 --> 23:53.813
I AM NOT FINISHED.

23:53.813 --> 23:54.974
YOU DON'T FEEL FINISHED

23:54.974 --> 23:57.226
BECAUSE THIS ISN'T
THE END FOR YOU.

23:57.226 --> 23:59.649
THERE IS NO FINISH LINE.

23:59.649 --> 24:01.230
THERE IS NO END POINT.

24:01.230 --> 24:02.612
♪ TALKING AWAY ♪

24:02.612 --> 24:04.654
YOU JUST HAVE TO GO.
I KNOW. I KNOW.

24:04.654 --> 24:08.067
I KNOW, A-AND I'M --
AND I KEEP TRYING TO,

24:08.067 --> 24:11.120
BUT I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO...JUST DO IT.

24:11.120 --> 24:12.662
♪ TODAY ISN'T MY DAY
TO FIND YOU ♪

24:12.662 --> 24:14.413
YOU GOT TO HELP ME, MER.

24:14.413 --> 24:17.456
DR. YANG, THE DONOR HEART
WAS DELAYED IN TRAFFIC.

24:17.456 --> 24:18.538
HOW LONG?
CAN'T SAY.

24:18.538 --> 24:20.880
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

24:20.880 --> 24:22.381
LET'S GO.

24:22.381 --> 24:24.544
[ SIGHS ]

24:24.544 --> 24:26.385
[ SIGHS, SNIFFLES ]

24:26.385 --> 24:27.927
OKAY?
OKAY.

24:30.259 --> 24:34.303
♪ TAKE ME ON ♪

24:34.303 --> 24:36.395
DEREK.

24:36.395 --> 24:38.648
GOODBYE.

24:38.648 --> 24:41.440
♪ I'LL BE GONE ♪

24:41.440 --> 24:42.481
GOODBYE.

24:42.481 --> 24:46.485
♪ IN A DAY OR TWO ♪

24:49.318 --> 24:53.412
♪ SO NEEDLESS TO SAY ♪

24:53.412 --> 24:55.374
♪ OF ODDS AND ENDS ♪

24:55.374 --> 24:58.417
♪ BUT I'LL BE STUMBLING AWAY ♪

24:58.417 --> 25:00.119
ANY MORE COME IN?

25:00.119 --> 25:02.421
NOT FOR A WHILE.

25:02.421 --> 25:04.293
IT'S NOT FAIR.

25:04.293 --> 25:05.625
WEBBER WAS WRONG.
MAYBE YOU JUST NEED TO --

25:05.625 --> 25:07.386
REALLY, SHANE?

25:07.386 --> 25:09.468
I HUNG ON HIS EVERY WORD
ALL YEAR.

25:09.468 --> 25:10.630
ALL OF US DID.

25:10.630 --> 25:13.052
HE'S THE GREATEST TEACHER
I HAVE EVER HAD,

25:13.052 --> 25:14.724
SO MAYBE IF IT WERE SOMEONE ELSE
SAYING THIS,

25:14.724 --> 25:16.305
I WOULDN'T BELIEVE THEM,
BUT WEBBER?

25:16.305 --> 25:19.348
I GOT TO FIND
WHAT I'M GOOD AT.

25:19.348 --> 25:21.270
AND I WILL.

25:21.270 --> 25:22.942
♪ I'LL BE GONE ♪

25:22.942 --> 25:25.524
YOU WILL. GOOD LUCK.

25:25.524 --> 25:31.741
♪ IN A DAY OR TWO ♪

25:31.741 --> 25:32.992
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

25:32.992 --> 25:35.244
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY,
EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

25:35.244 --> 25:36.325
WHAT HAPPENED?

25:36.325 --> 25:37.456
THERE WAS AN EXPLOSION.

25:37.456 --> 25:41.420
BUT IT'S OVER,
AND YOU'RE FINE, OKAY?

25:41.420 --> 25:42.752
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE.

25:42.752 --> 25:45.334
[ SIGHS ]

25:45.334 --> 25:48.087
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH ♪

25:48.087 --> 25:51.380
♪ OH-OH-OH-OH ♪

25:51.380 --> 25:54.634
♪ OH-OH-OH-OH ♪

25:54.634 --> 25:57.386
♪ OOH ♪

25:57.386 --> 26:03.232
♪ OH, THINGS THAT YOU SAY ♪

26:03.232 --> 26:07.066
♪ IS IT A LIFE OR JUST
TO PLAY MY WORRIES AWAY? ♪

26:07.066 --> 26:09.278
THE PATIENT
IN BED FOUR IS AWAKE.

26:09.278 --> 26:10.990
THANK YOU.

26:10.990 --> 26:15.955
♪ YOU'RE ALL THE THINGS
I'VE GOT TO REMEMBER ♪

26:15.955 --> 26:19.288
♪ YOU'RE SHYING AWAY ♪

26:19.288 --> 26:21.911
♪ IT'S NO BETTER
TO BE SAFE THAN SORRY ♪

26:21.911 --> 26:23.292
Bailey: I WOULD HAVE THOUGHT,
YOU KNOW,

26:23.292 --> 26:25.334
NOW THAT YOU'RE MINISTER
OF EDUCATION OR WHATEVER

26:25.334 --> 26:26.706
THAT YOU COULD TELL
THE STUPID BOARD --

26:26.706 --> 26:28.207
I DON'T CONTROL
THE BUDGET, BAILEY.

26:28.207 --> 26:30.840
W-WELL, DID YOU AT LEAST FIGHT
FOR ME TO KEEP MY LAB?

26:30.840 --> 26:32.131
NO, I DID NOT.

26:32.131 --> 26:33.713
NOW, WHEN IT CAME TIME
THIS MORNING

26:33.713 --> 26:35.344
TO DECIDE WHO WOULD STAFF
THE O.R.s,

26:35.344 --> 26:37.346
WHO HAD THE STAMINA
AND THE TALENT

26:37.346 --> 26:39.679
TO RUN PATIENT AFTER PATIENT,
IT WAS A NO-BRAINER.

26:39.679 --> 26:42.021
I MEAN, SOME PEOPLE BELONG
BEHIND A MICROSCOPE,

26:42.021 --> 26:43.222
BUT YOU DON'T.

26:43.222 --> 26:44.523
YOU ARE A SURGEON,
BAILEY.

26:44.523 --> 26:46.485
IT IS WHAT
I TRAINED YOU TO BE.
[ GROANS ]

26:46.485 --> 26:49.278
AND ANYTHING ELSE
WOULD BE A WASTE OF YOUR TIME.

26:49.278 --> 26:51.190
AND BEFORE YOU CONTINUE
TRASHING THE BOARD,

26:51.190 --> 26:52.992
YOU OUGHT TO KNOW THAT YANG
IS LEAVING A SEAT OPEN,

26:52.992 --> 26:54.323
AND I'M RECOMMENDING YOU,

26:54.323 --> 26:58.367
WHICH THE BOARD WILL AGREE
IS ALSO A NO-BRAINER.

26:58.367 --> 27:00.239
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

27:00.239 --> 27:01.450
OH.

27:01.450 --> 27:03.743
W-WELL, THAT'S --

27:03.743 --> 27:05.915
DR. BAILEY, UM, DR. WEBBER,
I-I JUST WANTED TO S--

27:05.915 --> 27:07.626
SHE DOESN'T HAVE TIME
FOR LONG GOODBYES.

27:07.626 --> 27:09.338
SHE HAS A PLANE TO CATCH.
NO, MER --

27:09.338 --> 27:10.419
WELL,
YOU SHOULD GO, THEN.

27:10.419 --> 27:11.961
YEAH, DON'T STAND
AROUND HERE TALKING.

27:11.961 --> 27:13.212
GO, BE A SURGEON.
THAT'S WHAT WE TRAINED YOU FOR.

27:13.212 --> 27:14.754
CAN I COME WITH YOU?

27:14.754 --> 27:16.635
SHANE, NOT NOW.
I'M NOT KIDDING.
TAKE ME TO SWITZERLAND.

27:16.635 --> 27:17.757
I CAN HELP YOU.

27:17.757 --> 27:19.598
YOU'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF YOUR RESIDENCY.

27:19.598 --> 27:22.391
AND MY TEACHER IS LEAVING,
THE ONE I WANT TO LEARN FROM,

27:22.391 --> 27:24.433
TO GO DO THE WORK
I WANT TO BE A PART OF.

27:24.433 --> 27:26.645
I WANT TO BE IN CHARGE
OF MY EDUCATION,

27:26.645 --> 27:27.767
AND I CHOOSE YOU.

27:27.767 --> 27:29.188
YOU CAN SAY NO,

27:29.188 --> 27:31.320
BUT I WILL BADGER YOU
UNTIL YOU SAY YES.

27:34.193 --> 27:36.866
YES.

27:36.866 --> 27:38.077
[ LAUGHS ]

27:38.077 --> 27:39.869
I QUIT.

27:39.869 --> 27:43.452
RESPECTFULLY.
AND THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING.

27:43.452 --> 27:45.164
REALLY.

27:47.496 --> 27:49.418
YES!

27:49.418 --> 27:51.250
Bailey: WANT TO GRAB
ANYTHING ELSE ON THE WAY OUT?

27:51.250 --> 27:53.843
C.T. MACHINE?

27:53.843 --> 27:56.595
WHAT -- OH! [ GRUNTS ]
THANK YOU.

28:03.803 --> 28:05.434
PROUD OF YOU.

28:07.306 --> 28:08.567
GO.

28:08.567 --> 28:10.359
OKAY, NOW. COME ON. LET'S GO.
WE HAVE TO GO.

28:10.359 --> 28:12.271
WAIT. WAIT.
WAIT HERE.

28:12.271 --> 28:14.313
CRISTINA,
WE GOT TO GO!

28:14.313 --> 28:17.026
UGH.

28:17.026 --> 28:18.367
Owen:
LAP PADS, MORE SUCTION.

28:18.367 --> 28:19.909
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
GET IN THERE, WARREN.

28:19.909 --> 28:22.371
I KNOW.
CLAMP IT...

28:22.371 --> 28:23.783
AND MAKE IT PRETTY LATER.

28:23.783 --> 28:26.125
WHERE'S THIS BLEEDING COMING
FROM? GET UNDERNEATH FOR ME.

28:26.125 --> 28:27.206
CLAMP.

28:27.206 --> 28:29.418
[ KNOCK ON WINDOW ]

28:29.418 --> 28:33.042
♪ YOU NEVER GET TO
GIVE IT ALL YOU GOT ♪

28:33.042 --> 28:37.336
♪ 'CAUSE YOU FORGOT
TO TAKE IT TO THE TOP ♪

28:37.336 --> 28:39.969
♪ OH, RUBY BLUE ♪

28:41.300 --> 28:43.803
♪ WHY DO YOU MAKE A START ♪

28:43.803 --> 28:46.475
♪ WITH NO MEANS TO GO ON? ♪

28:46.475 --> 28:50.229
♪ IT'S ON THE TIP OF YOUR ♪

28:50.229 --> 28:53.562
♪ RUBY, WE USED TO
LOVE YOU TRULY ♪

28:53.562 --> 28:54.904
♪ YOU USED TO MAKE US LAUGH ♪

28:54.904 --> 28:56.355
GOOD. CLAMP.

28:56.355 --> 28:58.737
♪ IT REALLY WAS A GAS ♪

28:58.737 --> 29:00.569
♪ NOW YOU'RE A BORE ♪

29:00.569 --> 29:04.323
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]

29:04.323 --> 29:06.956
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.
THAT'S GOOD. GO AHEAD.

29:06.956 --> 29:09.248
LET'S GO --
NOW, OR YOU NEVER WILL.

29:09.248 --> 29:12.251
WAIT. YOU -- YOU ALREADY
CALLED ME A CAB?

29:12.251 --> 29:13.462
NO.

29:14.924 --> 29:16.966
WAIT. WAIT.
IS THAT FOR LINK McNEIL?

29:16.966 --> 29:18.377
YEAH.
I NEED TO FIND DR. YANG.

29:18.377 --> 29:20.299
I'M DR. YANG.
NO! YOU NEED TO FIND
DR. PIERCE.

29:20.299 --> 29:21.801
YOU CAN GO
TO THE NURSE'S STATION,

29:21.801 --> 29:22.882
AND THEY WILL DIRECT YOU.

29:22.882 --> 29:25.344
MEREDITH, NO!
I-I CAN'T JUST LEAVE THEM.

29:25.344 --> 29:27.386
YES, YOU CAN.
THEY ARE IN GOOD HANDS.

29:27.386 --> 29:28.727
PIERCE IS GONNA DO IT,

29:28.727 --> 29:30.349
AND SABINE KNOWS SHE'S GONNA
DO IT. SHE CONSENTED.

29:30.349 --> 29:32.561
OWEN IS HERE,
I AM HERE,

29:32.561 --> 29:34.984
AND WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW UP
WITH LINK POST-OP, OKAY?

29:34.984 --> 29:36.445
GET TO THE AIRPORT
AS FAST AS YOU CAN.

29:36.445 --> 29:38.027
WAIT. MEREDITH.
WHAT?

29:38.027 --> 29:40.739
WHAT DO YOU NEED,
AN "I LOVE YOU" OR SOMETHING?

29:42.661 --> 29:44.493
I LOVE YOU.

29:44.493 --> 29:46.365
CALL ME
WHEN YOU GET THERE.

29:46.365 --> 29:47.827
♪ FIVE AND SIX ♪

29:49.999 --> 29:51.330
♪ WHO WOULD HAVE BELIEVED ♪

29:51.330 --> 29:57.416
♪ IT WOULD COME TO THIS? ♪

29:57.416 --> 30:01.130
♪ LOOK WHAT YOU DO,
OH, RUBY BLUE ♪

30:01.130 --> 30:03.342
[ SIGHS ]

30:06.515 --> 30:09.598
♪ LOOK WHAT YOU DO,
OH, RUBY BLUE ♪

30:14.233 --> 30:16.105
YOU OKAY?

30:16.105 --> 30:17.606
I JUST FEEL BAD.

30:17.606 --> 30:18.647
DID YOU LOSE SOMEONE?

30:20.069 --> 30:24.823
NO, NO, I-I DIDN'T LOSE
A SINGLE ONE.

30:24.823 --> 30:28.157
THAT'S WHY I FEEL BAD --
'CAUSE I FEEL SO GOOD.

30:28.157 --> 30:30.749
THIS IS THE THING,
MEREDITH.

30:30.749 --> 30:32.751
THIS IS WHAT IT FEELS LIKE.

30:32.751 --> 30:33.752
IT FEELS LIKE --

30:33.752 --> 30:35.915
CANDY.
BUT WITH BLOOD.

30:35.915 --> 30:38.547
ONLY SO MUCH BETTER.
AND DEREK --

30:38.547 --> 30:41.130
I MEAN, I WAS STILL
IN HIS SHADOW,

30:41.130 --> 30:42.591
BUT I DIDN'T EVEN CARE.

30:42.591 --> 30:44.263
AND THE ONLY THING
THAT WOULD HAVE MADE IT BETTER

30:44.263 --> 30:47.176
WAS IF HIS SHADOW WAS GONE,
SO YOU GUYS CAN GO.

30:47.176 --> 30:49.058
HAVE FUN.
BE HAPPY.

30:49.058 --> 30:51.100
Meredith:
WHAT THE HECK?

30:51.100 --> 30:52.771
CRISTINA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

30:54.853 --> 30:57.066
Cristina: I CAN'T GO.
YES, YOU CAN!

30:57.066 --> 30:58.397
WE HAVE TO FINISH.

30:58.397 --> 31:00.069
YOU'RE GONNA MISS YOUR --
WE HAVE TO DANCE IT OUT.

31:00.069 --> 31:01.570
THAT'S HOW WE FINISH.

31:01.570 --> 31:04.323
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

31:04.323 --> 31:05.905
[ SIGHS ]

31:05.905 --> 31:07.326
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:07.326 --> 31:11.200
WHAT, YOU GONNA CALL SOMEONE
TO MAKE ME LEAVE OR WHAT --

31:11.200 --> 31:12.751
I'M FINDING A SONG.

31:14.914 --> 31:16.085
[ SIGHS ]

31:19.838 --> 31:21.760
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

31:21.760 --> 31:23.132
OKAY, READY?
WAIT.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.385
WE'LL CALL EACH OTHER
AT LEAST TWICE A MONTH,

31:26.385 --> 31:27.927
AND -- AND WE'LL TEXT
ALL THE TIME.

31:27.927 --> 31:29.768
YOU HATE TEXTING.
TEXT ME.

31:29.768 --> 31:32.011
AND DON'T LET OWEN
GET ALL DARK AND TWISTY.
TAKE CARE OF HIM.

31:32.011 --> 31:33.182
AND ALEX --
TAKE CARE OF ALEX.

31:33.182 --> 31:35.274
HE NEEDS TO BE MOCKED
AT LEAST ONCE A DAY,

31:35.274 --> 31:37.316
OR HE'LL BE INSUFFERABLE.

31:37.316 --> 31:40.439
DON'T GET ON ANY LITTLE,
TINY PLANES THAT CAN CRASH

31:40.439 --> 31:42.861
OR STICK YOUR HAND
IN A BODY CAVITY

31:42.861 --> 31:44.023
THAT HAS A BOMB IN IT

31:44.023 --> 31:45.945
OR OFFER YOUR
LIFE TO A GUNMAN!

31:45.945 --> 31:47.446
DON'T DO THAT.

31:50.029 --> 31:53.032
DON'T BE A HERO.

31:53.032 --> 31:55.294
YOU'RE MY PERSON.

31:55.294 --> 31:56.996
I NEED YOU ALIVE.

31:56.996 --> 31:58.457
YOU MAKE ME BRAVE.

32:02.131 --> 32:04.753
OKAY.

32:04.753 --> 32:06.305
NOW WE DANCE IT OUT.

32:06.305 --> 32:09.008
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

32:10.049 --> 32:14.603
[ "WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO"
PLAYS ]

32:14.603 --> 32:17.856
♪ WHERE DO YOU GO
WITH YOUR BROKEN HEART IN TOW? ♪

32:17.856 --> 32:19.108
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:19.108 --> 32:23.692
♪ WHAT DO YOU DO
WITH THE LEFTOVER YOU? ♪

32:23.692 --> 32:26.945
♪ AND HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHEN TO LET GO? ♪

32:26.945 --> 32:28.367
YOU LOVE THIS SONG!

32:28.367 --> 32:29.989
♪ WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO? ♪

32:29.989 --> 32:33.372
♪ WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO? ♪

32:33.372 --> 32:35.034
♪ LOOK ME IN THE EYE ♪

32:35.034 --> 32:38.077
♪ AND TELL ME
YOU DON'T FIND ME ATTRACTIVE ♪

32:38.077 --> 32:41.960
♪ LOOK ME IN THE HEART
AND TELL ME YOU WON'T GO ♪

32:41.960 --> 32:43.582
♪ LOOK ME IN THE EYE ♪

32:43.582 --> 32:46.925
♪ AND PROMISE
NO LOVE'S LIKE OUR LOVE ♪

32:46.925 --> 32:49.928
♪ LOOK ME IN THE HEART
AND UNBREAK BROKEN ♪

32:49.928 --> 32:51.140
♪ IT WON'T HAPPEN ♪

32:51.140 --> 32:53.642
♪ IT'S LOVE THAT LEAVES ♪

32:53.642 --> 32:57.436
♪ AND BREAKS
THE SEAL OF ALWAYS ♪

32:57.436 --> 33:00.979
♪ THINKING
YOU WOULD BE REAL ♪

33:00.979 --> 33:05.104
♪ HAPPY AND HEALTHY,
STRONG AND CALM ♪

33:05.104 --> 33:07.026
♪ WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO? ♪

33:07.026 --> 33:09.568
♪ WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO? ♪

33:09.568 --> 33:13.032
♪ WHERE DO YOU GO
WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE ♪

33:13.032 --> 33:14.873
♪ AND THE WORLD KNOWS ♪

33:14.873 --> 33:17.076
♪ HOW DO YOU LIVE SO HAPPILY ♪

33:17.076 --> 33:20.169
♪ WHILE I AM SAD
AND BROKEN DOWN? ♪

33:20.169 --> 33:21.250
I GOT TO GO.

33:23.001 --> 33:24.293
YOU STAY HERE, OKAY?

33:24.293 --> 33:25.754
OKAY.

33:25.754 --> 33:28.127
♪ WHERE DOES THE GOOD GO? ♪

33:28.127 --> 33:29.798
♪ LOOK ME IN THE EYE ♪

33:29.798 --> 33:32.431
♪ AND TELL ME
YOU DON'T FIND ME ATTRACTIVE ♪

33:32.431 --> 33:37.306
YOU ARE A GIFTED SURGEON
WITH AN EXTRAORDINARY MIND.

33:37.306 --> 33:39.808
DON'T LET WHAT HE WANTS
ECLIPSE WHAT YOU NEED.

33:39.808 --> 33:44.022
HE'S VERY DREAMY.
BUT HE IS NOT THE SUN.

33:44.022 --> 33:46.065
YOU ARE.

33:46.065 --> 33:48.777
♪ IT'S LOVE THAT LEAVES ♪

33:48.777 --> 33:52.201
♪ AND BREAKS
THE SEAL OF ALWAYS ♪

33:52.201 --> 33:55.654
♪ THINKING
YOU WOULD BE REAL ♪

33:55.654 --> 33:58.157
Derek: [ SIGHS ]
THEY'RE ASLEEP.

33:58.157 --> 33:59.958
DID YOU GET THOSE
SIGNED?

34:01.790 --> 34:03.792
MEREDITH,
YOU'LL TALK TO HER TOMORROW.

34:03.792 --> 34:05.924
KNOWING YOU GUYS,
YOU'LL TALK EVERY DAY.

34:07.836 --> 34:11.130
NO, IT'S NOT --

34:11.130 --> 34:12.381
I DON'T THINK
I CAN SIGN THIS.

34:12.381 --> 34:13.762
SORRY,
I KNOW YOU'RE WIPED,

34:13.762 --> 34:15.174
BUT I NEED TO HAVE THOSE
ON THE PLANE BY 7:00.

34:15.174 --> 34:16.435
NO, I DON'T --

34:18.267 --> 34:19.848
I THINK
I NEED TO STAY HERE.

34:22.851 --> 34:24.773
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

34:28.447 --> 34:30.399
DR. TORRES?

34:30.399 --> 34:31.690
UM, THE BABY'S PARENTS
ARE HERE,

34:31.690 --> 34:33.031
AND THEY WERE WONDERING
IF LEANNE WAS UP TO --

34:33.031 --> 34:34.283
YES, YES.
PLEASE, YES.

34:34.283 --> 34:35.954
YEAH? OKAY.
YEAH, COME IN.

34:37.996 --> 34:39.408
[ SNIFFLES ]

34:39.408 --> 34:41.540
[ Crying ]
HEY, LEANNE.

34:41.540 --> 34:42.791
ARE YOU OKAY?

34:42.791 --> 34:43.912
IS SHE OKAY?

34:43.912 --> 34:45.544
DO YOU GUYS LOVE HER?
IS SHE ALL RIGHT?

34:45.544 --> 34:47.796
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.
SHE'S PERFECT.

34:47.796 --> 34:49.508
[ SNIFFLES ]
THANK YOU.

34:49.508 --> 34:52.671
[ Voice breaking ]
WE'RE SO GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

34:53.762 --> 34:55.134
[ SNIFFLES ]

34:55.134 --> 34:56.265
ARE YOU OKAY?

34:56.265 --> 34:58.767
YEAH. THAT'S JUST --
IT'S REALLY SWEET.

34:58.767 --> 35:00.639
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:00.639 --> 35:02.141
IT'S REALLY AMAZING.

35:02.141 --> 35:04.893
I WONDER WHY THEY WANTED
A SURROGATE.

35:04.893 --> 35:07.646
I WONDER IF --
I WONDER IF SHE COULDN'T --

35:07.646 --> 35:10.899
SHE REALLY HELPED THEM.
SHE REALLY LIKES THEM.

35:10.899 --> 35:12.901
THAT'S REALLY AMAZING,
RIGHT?

35:18.036 --> 35:19.368
[ SIGHS ]

35:25.083 --> 35:26.915
[ BOTH SIGH ]

35:30.379 --> 35:34.092
GUESS WHAT.
I DELIVERED A BABY TODAY.

35:34.092 --> 35:35.424
AND THE GOOD NEWS IS,

35:35.424 --> 35:37.556
IF THE O.B. DOESN'T SHOW UP
FOR OURS, THEN I GET --

35:37.556 --> 35:39.017
HEY.

35:40.929 --> 35:43.892
[ SNIFFLES ]
OUR BABY WILL BE FINE.

35:43.892 --> 35:44.973
HE'LL BE FINE --

35:44.973 --> 35:47.896
OR SHE WILL BE
'CAUSE SHE'LL HAVE US.

35:47.896 --> 35:50.028
HEY, OF COURSE SHE WILL.

35:50.028 --> 35:52.070
YOU KNOW,
MY MOM ALWAYS SAYS

35:52.070 --> 35:54.112
THAT'S
HOW THE WORLD CHANGES.

35:54.112 --> 35:56.235
GOOD PEOPLE RAISING
THEIR BABIES RIGHT.

35:56.235 --> 35:57.906
WAIT, IS THAT --
IS THAT A THING?

35:57.906 --> 35:59.738
I THOUGHT THAT WAS
JUST MY MOM.

36:06.995 --> 36:08.547
I LOVE YOU.

36:12.291 --> 36:14.383
IT WENT PERFECTLY.

36:14.383 --> 36:18.006
LINK'S HEART IS RESPONDING WELL,
AND SO IS HE.

36:18.006 --> 36:20.178
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

36:20.178 --> 36:21.260
MY PLEASURE.

36:21.260 --> 36:22.801
NOW, I KNOW FROM DR. YANG

36:22.801 --> 36:25.183
THAT YOU'VE HEARD THE WHOLE
ANTI-REJECTION SPIEL BEFORE...

36:25.183 --> 36:29.978
♪ SET THEM FREE
AT THE BREAK OF DAWN ♪

36:29.978 --> 36:34.483
♪ TILL ONE BY ONE,
THEY WERE ALL GONE ♪

36:34.483 --> 36:36.945
♪ BACK AT BASE,
BUGS IN THE SOFTWARE ♪
[ DOG BARKS ]

36:36.945 --> 36:39.578
OOH! I DON'T WANT TO GET
TOO EXCITED.

36:39.578 --> 36:42.030
YANG'S BODY
ISN'T EVEN COLD YET, BUT --

36:42.030 --> 36:45.123
NO, YOU CAN --
YOU CAN BE EXCITED.

36:45.123 --> 36:46.915
[ Laughing ]
YOU GOT A PLACE ON THE BOARD!

36:46.915 --> 36:48.667
AH!

36:48.667 --> 36:51.380
I WILL MAKE POLICY,
NOT JUST HEAR IT.

36:51.380 --> 36:53.422
I WILL MAKE CHANGES.

36:53.422 --> 36:55.043
YOU CAN KEEP
YOUR GENOME LAB.

36:55.043 --> 36:56.505
WE CAN HAVE
A GENOME THEME PARK.

36:56.505 --> 36:57.886
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

36:57.886 --> 36:59.298
AND...[SIGHS]

36:59.298 --> 37:00.639
IT'S JUST...

37:02.511 --> 37:03.682
WHAT?

37:05.724 --> 37:07.976
WEBBER PICKED ME.

37:07.976 --> 37:11.810
♪ 99 RED BALLOONS ♪
[ LAUGHS ]

37:11.810 --> 37:13.111
UGH!

37:13.111 --> 37:14.443
BOY, GET IN THERE DEEP,
DEEP, DEEP.

37:14.443 --> 37:15.814
OH, YEAH, I GOT YOU.
I GOT YOU.

37:15.814 --> 37:17.816
♪ PANIC, LADS ♪

37:17.816 --> 37:19.988
OW.
WHAT -- WHAT IS THIS?

37:19.988 --> 37:21.740
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT IS --

37:21.740 --> 37:24.493
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S FROM YANG.

37:24.493 --> 37:29.077
♪ THE WAR MACHINE
SPRINGS TO LIFE ♪

37:29.077 --> 37:32.130
♪ OPENS UP ONE EAGER EYE ♪

37:32.130 --> 37:33.251
ALEX, WHAT?

37:33.251 --> 37:34.833
IT'S CRISTINA'S SHARES
IN THE HOSPITAL.

37:34.833 --> 37:36.755
♪ FOCUSING IT ON THE SKY ♪

37:36.755 --> 37:38.337
SHE'S LEAVING THEM TO ME.

37:38.337 --> 37:39.338
WHAT?

37:39.338 --> 37:41.049
SHE LEFT ME HER SEAT
ON THE BOARD.

37:41.049 --> 37:41.930
CAN SHE DO THAT?

37:41.930 --> 37:44.513
I DON'T KNOW.

37:44.513 --> 37:45.764
SHE DID.

37:45.764 --> 37:47.015
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:53.812 --> 37:55.063
Derek:
I TOOK THE JOB!

37:55.063 --> 37:57.356
AND YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO BE STEPPING BACK.

37:57.356 --> 37:59.818
YOU SAID, "TAKE THIS YEAR
AND MAKE IT COUNT.

37:59.818 --> 38:01.820
AND I'LL MAKE SURE
YOU CAN DO IT."
AND YOU LIED!

38:01.820 --> 38:03.241
SORRY. I LIED.

38:03.241 --> 38:04.953
IT'S A ONCE-IN-A-LIFETIME
OPPORTUNITY.

38:04.953 --> 38:07.165
SO, YOU GOT THIS THING,
AND I GAVE UP THAT PIECE.

38:07.165 --> 38:09.167
AND I FOUND A WAY
TO MAKE IT WORK

38:09.167 --> 38:11.410
WITH MY JOB, MY KIDS,
AND MY RESEARCH

38:11.410 --> 38:13.502
WITH LESS HELP FROM YOU,
AND I DID IT.
YOU'RE NOT A VICTIM.

38:13.502 --> 38:15.914
I'M KILLING MYSELF
JUST AS MUCH AS YOU ARE.

38:15.914 --> 38:17.295
AND THEN YOU WANTED MORE PIECES
AND MORE PIECES.
I'M FLYING BACK AND FORTH
ACROSS THE COUNTRY...

38:17.295 --> 38:19.047
TWICE A WEEK...
AND NOW THIS IS
JUST TOO MUCH.

38:19.047 --> 38:20.629
...SO I CAN SPEND TIME
WITH MY KIDS...
YOU CAN'T
JUST DRAG US AWAY...

38:20.629 --> 38:21.880
...AND BE A GOOD FATHER.
SO I CAN COME LIVE
IN YOUR SHADOW.

38:21.880 --> 38:23.091
"SHADOW"?
YOU HAVE A JOB.

38:23.091 --> 38:24.723
YOU'RE GONNA BE WORKING
AT JAMES MADISON.

38:24.723 --> 38:26.635
RIGHT, THAT'S HOW MY FATHER
GOT HIS FIRST JOB HERE.

38:26.635 --> 38:28.186
THEY WANTED MY MOM,

38:28.186 --> 38:31.059
SO SHE HAD TO CALL
THE UNIVERSITY AND
PULL SOME STRINGS

38:31.059 --> 38:33.432
AND FIND SOMETHING
FOR THATCHER TO DO.

38:33.432 --> 38:35.143
IT'S CALLED
A TRAILING SPOUSE.

38:35.143 --> 38:36.435
THIS IS NOT LIKE THAT.

38:36.435 --> 38:37.856
THIS IS EXACTLY THAT.

38:37.856 --> 38:39.698
AND IT'S NOT
WHAT I SIGNED UP FOR.

38:39.698 --> 38:41.069
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE -- YOU'RE BEING SELFISH.

38:41.069 --> 38:43.151
WELL, I HAVE TO BE, DEREK,
BECAUSE YOU BELIEVE

38:43.151 --> 38:45.153
THAT YOUR CAREER
IS MORE IMPORTANT THAN MINE.

38:45.153 --> 38:47.075
AT THIS MOMENT IN TIME,
IT IS!

38:47.075 --> 38:49.117
NO, NOT AT THIS MOMENT --
ALWAYS.

38:49.117 --> 38:51.159
YOU WILL ALWAYS BE
THAT HOT-SHOT SURGEON,

38:51.159 --> 38:53.582
AND I WILL ALWAYS BE
THAT YOUNG INTERN WHO
FELL IN LOVE WITH YOU.

38:53.582 --> 38:55.874
IF THAT'S HOW YOU SEE
YOURSELF, THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING ABOUT THAT.

38:55.874 --> 38:59.628
THAT IS NOT HOW I SEE MYSELF.
THAT IS THE ISSUE HERE.

38:59.628 --> 39:01.590
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

39:01.590 --> 39:04.092
D.C. --
YOU CAN DO YOUR SURGERIES,

39:04.092 --> 39:06.965
YOU CAN DO YOUR RESEARCH,
YOU CAN DO THE PORTAL VEINS.

39:06.965 --> 39:08.927
THERE IS NOTHING YOU CAN DO HERE
THAT YOU CAN'T DO THERE.

39:08.927 --> 39:11.059
BUT I DON'T WANT TO!
[ SIGHS ]

39:11.059 --> 39:12.971
WE'RE NOT JUST TALKING
ABOUT MY JOB, DEREK.

39:12.971 --> 39:14.232
WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT MY LIFE.

39:14.232 --> 39:16.935
I GREW UP HERE.
I MADE MY FAMILY HERE.

39:16.935 --> 39:18.817
I HELPED TO REBUILD
THE HOSPITAL HERE

39:18.817 --> 39:20.399
THAT HAS
MY SISTER'S NAME ON IT,

39:20.399 --> 39:22.030
MY MOTHER'S NAME,
MY NAME.

39:22.030 --> 39:24.242
I LIVE HERE.
MY LIFE IS HERE.

39:24.242 --> 39:26.405
I DON'T WANT TO LEAVE.

39:26.405 --> 39:31.620
Cristina: WHENEVER WE THINK
WE KNOW THE FUTURE...

39:31.620 --> 39:35.043
EVEN FOR A SECOND...

39:35.043 --> 39:36.495
IT CHANGES.

39:36.495 --> 39:39.337
DR. PIERCE.
ROUGH DAY, HUH?

39:39.337 --> 39:40.759
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:40.759 --> 39:41.920
SEVEN TRAUMAS,

39:41.920 --> 39:43.922
TWO OF WHICH HAD
RIGHT VENTRICULAR PERFS,

39:43.922 --> 39:47.135
TOPPED OFF WITH
A PEDIATRIC HEART TRANSPLANT.

39:47.135 --> 39:48.427
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

39:48.427 --> 39:50.098
OTHER THAN THAT,
HOW YOU SETTLING IN?

39:50.098 --> 39:53.101
[ LAUGHS ]

39:53.101 --> 39:56.685
IT HAS BEEN THE WEIRDEST
TWO WEEKS OF MY LIFE.

39:56.685 --> 39:59.728
I DON'T KNOW ANYONE.
NO ONE KNOWS ME.

39:59.728 --> 40:04.402
I HAVEN'T HAD ONE CONVERSATION
THAT WASN'T RELATED TO WORK.

40:04.402 --> 40:05.574
[ SIGHS ]

40:05.574 --> 40:07.365
WELL...

40:07.365 --> 40:09.117
YOU KNOW ME NOW.

40:09.117 --> 40:10.328
NO. [CHUCKLES]

40:10.328 --> 40:13.912
GOD, I SOUND LIKE A KID
CRYING AT CAMP.

40:13.912 --> 40:15.163
NO, IT'S NOT --
IT'S NOT THAT.

40:15.163 --> 40:17.746
IT'S...SOMETHING ELSE.

40:19.748 --> 40:22.461
I WAS ADOPTED.

40:22.461 --> 40:24.883
TWO YEARS AGO,
I LOOKED UP MY BIRTH MOM.

40:24.883 --> 40:27.045
I HAD TO GO TO THE COURT
FOR THE RECORDS.

40:27.045 --> 40:30.809
SHE'S DEAD NOW, UM,
SO I COULD ONLY GET HER NAME.

40:30.809 --> 40:34.182
BUT SHE WAS AMAZING.

40:34.933 --> 40:37.015
SHE WAS A SURGEON HERE.

40:37.015 --> 40:39.558
HER NAME IS
ALL OVER THIS HOSPITAL.

40:39.558 --> 40:41.690
THAT'S NOT WHY
I TOOK THE JOB.

40:41.690 --> 40:44.483
I MEAN, IT'S A LITTLE BIT WHY
I INTERVIEWED,

40:44.483 --> 40:47.365
BUT IT'S JUST...
SO WEIRD.

40:50.909 --> 40:54.122
W-WHAT WAS HER NAME?

40:54.122 --> 40:55.333
YOUR BIRTH MOTHER.

40:55.333 --> 40:58.416
ELLIS GREY.

40:58.416 --> 41:00.128
DID YOU KNOW HER?

41:00.128 --> 41:04.252
SOMETIMES THE FUTURE CHANGES
QUICKLY AND COMPLETELY...

41:06.885 --> 41:10.258
...AND WE'RE LEFT ONLY WITH
THE CHOICE OF WHAT TO DO NEXT.

41:10.258 --> 41:13.091
Derek: YOU'RE ASKING ME
TO CHOOSE BETWEEN THIS JOB...

41:13.091 --> 41:14.933
AND MY FAMILY?

41:14.933 --> 41:19.648
I AM SIMPLY SAYING
I AM NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

41:19.648 --> 41:22.981
I AM STAYING HERE.

41:22.981 --> 41:25.313
WE CAN CHOOSE
TO BE AFRAID OF IT...

41:25.313 --> 41:26.695
[ SIGHS ]

41:26.695 --> 41:30.368
TO STAND THERE, TREMBLING...

41:30.368 --> 41:32.611
NOT MOVING...

